94// static
95std::string Driver::GetResourcesPath(StringRef BinaryPath,
96 StringRef CustomResourceDir) {
97 // Since the resource directory is embedded in the module hash, it's important
98 // that all places that need it call this function, so that they get the
99 // exact same string ("a/../b/" and "b/" get different hashes, for example).
100
101 // Dir is bin/ or lib/, depending on where BinaryPath is.
102 std::string Dir = llvm::sys::path::parent_path(BinaryPath);
103
104 SmallString<128> P(Dir);
105 if (CustomResourceDir != "") {
106 llvm::sys::path::append(P, CustomResourceDir);
107 } else {
108 // On Windows, libclang.dll is in bin/.
109 // On non-Windows, libclang.so/.dylib is in lib/.
110 // With a static-library build of libclang, LibClangPath will contain the
111 // path of the embedding binary, which for LLVM binaries will be in bin/.
112 // ../lib gets us to lib/ in both cases.
113 P = llvm::sys::path::parent_path(Dir);
114 llvm::sys::path::append(P, Twine("lib") + CLANG_LIBDIR_SUFFIX, "clang",
115 CLANG_VERSION_STRING);
116 }
117
118 return P.str();
119}

121Driver::Driver(StringRef ClangExecutable, StringRef TargetTriple,
122 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
123 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> VFS)
124 : Opts(createDriverOptTable()), Diags(Diags), VFS(std::move(VFS)),
125 Mode(GCCMode), SaveTemps(SaveTempsNone), BitcodeEmbed(EmbedNone),
126 LTOMode(LTOK_None), ClangExecutable(ClangExecutable),
127 SysRoot(DEFAULT_SYSROOT), DriverTitle("clang LLVM compiler"),
128 CCPrintOptionsFilename(nullptr), CCPrintHeadersFilename(nullptr),
129 CCLogDiagnosticsFilename(nullptr), CCCPrintBindings(false),
130 CCPrintOptions(false), CCPrintHeaders(false), CCLogDiagnostics(false),
131 CCGenDiagnostics(false), TargetTriple(TargetTriple),
132 CCCGenericGCCName(""), Saver(Alloc), CheckInputsExist(true),
133 GenReproducer(false), SuppressMissingInputWarning(false) {
134
135 // Provide a sane fallback if no VFS is specified.
136 if (!this->VFS)
137 this->VFS = llvm::vfs::createPhysicalFileSystem().release();
138
139 Name = llvm::sys::path::filename(ClangExecutable);
140 Dir = llvm::sys::path::parent_path(ClangExecutable);
141 InstalledDir = Dir; // Provide a sensible default installed dir.
142
143#if defined(CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_SYSTEM_DIR)
144 SystemConfigDir = CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_SYSTEM_DIR;
145#endif
146#if defined(CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_USER_DIR)
147 UserConfigDir = CLANG_CONFIG_FILE_USER_DIR;
148#endif
149
150 // Compute the path to the resource directory.
151 ResourceDir = GetResourcesPath(ClangExecutable, CLANG_RESOURCE_DIR);
152}

154void Driver::ParseDriverMode(StringRef ProgramName,
155 ArrayRef<const char *> Args) {
156 if (ClangNameParts.isEmpty())
157 ClangNameParts = ToolChain::getTargetAndModeFromProgramName(ProgramName);
158 setDriverModeFromOption(ClangNameParts.DriverMode);
159
160 for (const char *ArgPtr : Args) {
161 // Ignore nullptrs, they are the response file's EOL markers.
162 if (ArgPtr == nullptr)
163 continue;
164 const StringRef Arg = ArgPtr;
165 setDriverModeFromOption(Arg);
166 }
167}
168
169void Driver::setDriverModeFromOption(StringRef Opt) {
170 const std::string OptName =
171 getOpts().getOption(options::OPT_driver_mode).getPrefixedName();
172 if (!Opt.startswith(OptName))
173 return;
174 StringRef Value = Opt.drop_front(OptName.size());
175
176 if (auto M = llvm::StringSwitch<llvm::Optional<DriverMode>>(Value)
177 .Case("gcc", GCCMode)
178 .Case("g++", GXXMode)
179 .Case("cpp", CPPMode)
180 .Case("cl", CLMode)
181 .Default(None))
182 Mode = *M;
183 else
184 Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument) << OptName << Value;
185}
186
187InputArgList Driver::ParseArgStrings(ArrayRef<const char *> ArgStrings,
188 bool IsClCompatMode,
189 bool &ContainsError) {
190 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Command line argument parsing");
191 ContainsError = false;
192
193 unsigned IncludedFlagsBitmask;
194 unsigned ExcludedFlagsBitmask;
195 std::tie(IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask) =
196 getIncludeExcludeOptionFlagMasks(IsClCompatMode);
197
198 unsigned MissingArgIndex, MissingArgCount;
199 InputArgList Args =
200 getOpts().ParseArgs(ArgStrings, MissingArgIndex, MissingArgCount,
201 IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask);
202
203 // Check for missing argument error.
204 if (MissingArgCount) {
205 Diag(diag::err_drv_missing_argument)
206 << Args.getArgString(MissingArgIndex) << MissingArgCount;
207 ContainsError |=
208 Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(diag::err_drv_missing_argument,
209 SourceLocation()) > DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
210 }
211
212 // Check for unsupported options.
213 for (const Arg *A : Args) {
214 if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::Unsupported)) {
215 unsigned DiagID;
216 auto ArgString = A->getAsString(Args);
217 std::string Nearest;
218 if (getOpts().findNearest(
219 ArgString, Nearest, IncludedFlagsBitmask,
220 ExcludedFlagsBitmask | options::Unsupported) > 1) {
221 DiagID = diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt;
222 Diag(DiagID) << ArgString;
223 } else {
224 DiagID = diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_with_suggestion;
225 Diag(DiagID) << ArgString << Nearest;
226 }
227 ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(DiagID, SourceLocation()) >
228 DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
229 continue;
230 }
231
232 // Warn about -mcpu= without an argument.
233 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mcpu_EQ) && A->containsValue("")) {
234 Diag(diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument) << A->getAsString(Args);
235 ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(
236 diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument,
237 SourceLocation()) > DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
238 }
239
240 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mabi_EQ)) {
241 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
242 A->claim();
243 if (Value == "sandbox") {
244 // output a warning that -mabi=sandbox is deprecated and replace with
245 // -mabi=purecap
246 Diag(diag::warn_cheri_sandbox_abi_is_purecap);
247 Args.append(
248 new Arg(Opts->getOption(options::OPT_mabi_EQ), "-mabi=",
249 A->getIndex(), "purecap"));
250 }
251 }
252 }
253
254 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_UNKNOWN)) {
255 unsigned DiagID;
256 auto ArgString = A->getAsString(Args);
257 std::string Nearest;
258 if (getOpts().findNearest(
259 ArgString, Nearest, IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask) > 1) {
260 DiagID = IsCLMode() ? diag::warn_drv_unknown_argument_clang_cl
261 : diag::err_drv_unknown_argument;
262 Diags.Report(DiagID) << ArgString;
263 } else {
264 DiagID = IsCLMode()
265 ? diag::warn_drv_unknown_argument_clang_cl_with_suggestion
266 : diag::err_drv_unknown_argument_with_suggestion;
267 Diags.Report(DiagID) << ArgString << Nearest;
268 }
269 ContainsError |= Diags.getDiagnosticLevel(DiagID, SourceLocation()) >
270 DiagnosticsEngine::Warning;
271 }
272
273 return Args;
274}

276// Determine which compilation mode we are in. We look for options which
277// affect the phase, starting with the earliest phases, and record which
278// option we used to determine the final phase.
279phases::ID Driver::getFinalPhase(const DerivedArgList &DAL,
280 Arg **FinalPhaseArg) const {
281 Arg *PhaseArg = nullptr;
282 phases::ID FinalPhase;
283
284 // -{E,EP,P,M,MM} only run the preprocessor.
285 if (CCCIsCPP() || (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_E)) ||
286 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP)) ||
287 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM)) ||
288 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_P))) {
289 FinalPhase = phases::Preprocess;
290
291 // --precompile only runs up to precompilation.
292 } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__precompile))) {
293 FinalPhase = phases::Precompile;
294
295 // -{fsyntax-only,-analyze,emit-ast} only run up to the compiler.
296 } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only)) ||
297 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_module_file_info)) ||
298 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_verify_pch)) ||
299 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc)) ||
300 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_rewrite_legacy_objc)) ||
301 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__migrate)) ||
302 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT__analyze,
303 options::OPT__analyze_auto)) ||
304 (PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_emit_ast))) {
305 FinalPhase = phases::Compile;
306
307 // -S only runs up to the backend.
308 } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_S))) {
309 FinalPhase = phases::Backend;
310
311 // -c compilation only runs up to the assembler.
312 } else if ((PhaseArg = DAL.getLastArg(options::OPT_c))) {
313 FinalPhase = phases::Assemble;
314
315 // Otherwise do everything.
316 } else
317 FinalPhase = phases::Link;
318
319 if (FinalPhaseArg)
320 *FinalPhaseArg = PhaseArg;
321
322 return FinalPhase;
323}
324
325static Arg *MakeInputArg(DerivedArgList &Args, OptTable &Opts,
326 StringRef Value, bool Claim = true) {
327 Arg *A = new Arg(Opts.getOption(options::OPT_INPUT), Value,
328 Args.getBaseArgs().MakeIndex(Value), Value.data());
329 Args.AddSynthesizedArg(A);
330 if (Claim)
331 A->claim();
332 return A;
333}
334
335DerivedArgList *Driver::TranslateInputArgs(const InputArgList &Args) const {
336 DerivedArgList *DAL = new DerivedArgList(Args);
337
338 bool HasNostdlib = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nostdlib);
339 bool HasNostdlibxx = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nostdlibxx);
340 bool HasNodefaultlib = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nodefaultlibs);
341 for (Arg *A : Args) {
342 // Unfortunately, we have to parse some forwarding options (-Xassembler,
343 // -Xlinker, -Xpreprocessor) because we either integrate their functionality
344 // (assembler and preprocessor), or bypass a previous driver ('collect2').
345
346 // Rewrite linker options, to replace --no-demangle with a custom internal
347 // option.
348 if ((A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Wl_COMMA) ||
349 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Xlinker)) &&
350 A->containsValue("--no-demangle")) {
351 // Add the rewritten no-demangle argument.
352 DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_Z_Xlinker__no_demangle));
353
354 // Add the remaining values as Xlinker arguments.
355 for (StringRef Val : A->getValues())
356 if (Val != "--no-demangle")
357 DAL->AddSeparateArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_Xlinker), Val);
358
359 continue;
360 }
361
362 // Rewrite preprocessor options, to replace -Wp,-MD,FOO which is used by
363 // some build systems. We don't try to be complete here because we don't
364 // care to encourage this usage model.
365 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Wp_COMMA) &&
366 (A->getValue(0) == StringRef("-MD") ||
367 A->getValue(0) == StringRef("-MMD"))) {
368 // Rewrite to -MD/-MMD along with -MF.
369 if (A->getValue(0) == StringRef("-MD"))
370 DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_MD));
371 else
372 DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_MMD));
373 if (A->getNumValues() == 2)
374 DAL->AddSeparateArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_MF),
375 A->getValue(1));
376 continue;
377 }
378
379 // Rewrite reserved library names.
380 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_l)) {
381 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
382
383 // Rewrite unless -nostdlib is present.
384 if (!HasNostdlib && !HasNodefaultlib && !HasNostdlibxx &&
385 Value == "stdc++") {
386 DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_Z_reserved_lib_stdcxx));
387 continue;
388 }
389
390 // Rewrite unconditionally.
391 if (Value == "cc_kext") {
392 DAL->AddFlagArg(A, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_Z_reserved_lib_cckext));
393 continue;
394 }
395 }
396
397 // Pick up inputs via the -- option.
398 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__DASH_DASH)) {
399 A->claim();
400 for (StringRef Val : A->getValues())
401 DAL->append(MakeInputArg(*DAL, *Opts, Val, false));
402 continue;
403 }
404
405 DAL->append(A);
406 }
407
408 // Enforce -static if -miamcu is present.
409 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_miamcu, options::OPT_mno_iamcu, false))
410 DAL->AddFlagArg(0, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_static));
411
412// Add a default value of -mlinker-version=, if one was given and the user
413// didn't specify one.
414#if defined(HOST_LINK_VERSION)
415 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mlinker_version_EQ) &&
416 strlen(HOST_LINK_VERSION) > 0) {
417 DAL->AddJoinedArg(0, Opts->getOption(options::OPT_mlinker_version_EQ),
418 HOST_LINK_VERSION);
419 DAL->getLastArg(options::OPT_mlinker_version_EQ)->claim();
420 }
421#endif
422
423 return DAL;
424}

426/// Compute target triple from args.
427///
428/// This routine provides the logic to compute a target triple from various
429/// args passed to the driver and the default triple string.
430static llvm::Triple computeTargetTriple(const Driver &D,
431 StringRef TargetTriple,
432 const ArgList &Args,
433 StringRef DarwinArchName = "") {
434 // FIXME: Already done in Compilation *Driver::BuildCompilation
435 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_target))
436 TargetTriple = A->getValue();
437
438 llvm::Triple Target(llvm::Triple::normalize(TargetTriple));
439
440 // GNU/Hurd's triples should have been -hurd-gnu*, but were historically made
441 // -gnu* only, and we can not change this, so we have to detect that case as
442 // being the Hurd OS.
443 if (TargetTriple.find("-unknown-gnu") != StringRef::npos ||
444 TargetTriple.find("-pc-gnu") != StringRef::npos)
445 Target.setOSName("hurd");
446
447 // Handle Apple-specific options available here.
448 if (Target.isOSBinFormatMachO()) {
449 // If an explicit Darwin arch name is given, that trumps all.
450 if (!DarwinArchName.empty()) {
451 tools::darwin::setTripleTypeForMachOArchName(Target, DarwinArchName);
452 return Target;
453 }
454
455 // Handle the Darwin '-arch' flag.
456 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_arch)) {
457 StringRef ArchName = A->getValue();
458 tools::darwin::setTripleTypeForMachOArchName(Target, ArchName);
459 }
460 }
461
462 // Handle pseudo-target flags '-mlittle-endian'/'-EL' and
463 // '-mbig-endian'/'-EB'.
464 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mlittle_endian,
465 options::OPT_mbig_endian)) {
466 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mlittle_endian)) {
467 llvm::Triple LE = Target.getLittleEndianArchVariant();
468 if (LE.getArch() != llvm::Triple::UnknownArch)
469 Target = std::move(LE);
470 } else {
471 llvm::Triple BE = Target.getBigEndianArchVariant();
472 if (BE.getArch() != llvm::Triple::UnknownArch)
473 Target = std::move(BE);
474 }
475 }
476
477 // Skip further flag support on OSes which don't support '-m32' or '-m64'.
478 if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::tce ||
479 Target.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Minix)
480 return Target;
481
482 // Handle pseudo-target flags '-m64', '-mx32', '-m32' and '-m16'.
483 Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_m64, options::OPT_mx32,
484 options::OPT_m32, options::OPT_m16);
485 if (A) {
486 llvm::Triple::ArchType AT = llvm::Triple::UnknownArch;
487
488 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m64)) {
489 AT = Target.get64BitArchVariant().getArch();
490 if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUX32)
491 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
492 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mx32) &&
493 Target.get64BitArchVariant().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64) {
494 AT = llvm::Triple::x86_64;
495 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUX32);
496 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m32)) {
497 AT = Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch();
498 if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUX32)
499 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
500 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m16) &&
501 Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86) {
502 AT = llvm::Triple::x86;
503 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::CODE16);
504 }
505
506 if (AT != llvm::Triple::UnknownArch && AT != Target.getArch())
507 Target.setArch(AT);
508 }
509
510 // Handle -miamcu flag.
511 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_miamcu, options::OPT_mno_iamcu, false)) {
512 if (Target.get32BitArchVariant().getArch() != llvm::Triple::x86)
513 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target) << "-miamcu"
514 << Target.str();
515
516 if (A && !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_m32))
517 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
518 << "-miamcu" << A->getBaseArg().getAsString(Args);
519
520 Target.setArch(llvm::Triple::x86);
521 Target.setArchName("i586");
522 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::UnknownEnvironment);
523 Target.setEnvironmentName("");
524 Target.setOS(llvm::Triple::ELFIAMCU);
525 Target.setVendor(llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor);
526 Target.setVendorName("intel");
527 }
528
529 // If target is MIPS adjust the target triple
530 // accordingly to provided ABI name.
531 A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mabi_EQ);
532 if (A && Target.isMIPS()) {
533 StringRef ABIName = A->getValue();
534 if (Target.isMIPS64() && Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap) {
535 if (ABIName.empty()) {
536 ABIName = "purecap";
537 } else if (ABIName != "purecap") {
538 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_abi_overriding_triple)
539 << Target.str() << Target.getEnvironmentName() << ABIName;
540 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUABI64);
541 }
542 }
543
544 if (ABIName == "32") {
545 Target = Target.get32BitArchVariant();
546 if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABI64 ||
547 Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABIN32)
548 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
549 } else if (ABIName == "n32") {
550 Target = Target.get64BitArchVariant();
551 if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNU ||
552 Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABI64 ||
553 Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap)
554 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUABIN32);
555 } else if (ABIName == "64") {
556 Target = Target.get64BitArchVariant();
557 if (Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNU ||
558 Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUABIN32 ||
559 Target.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap)
560 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUABI64);
561 } else if (ABIName == "purecap") {
562 if (Target.getEnvironment() != llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap && Target.getEnvironment() != llvm::Triple::UnknownEnvironment) {
563 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_abi_overriding_triple)
564 << Target.str() << Target.getEnvironmentName() << ABIName;
565 }
566 Target.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap);
567 if (Target.isMIPS32())
568 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target) << "-mabi=purecap" << Target.str();
569 if (Target.getSubArch() == llvm::Triple::NoSubArch) {
570 const char *ArchName = nullptr;
571 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_cheri, options::OPT_cheri_EQ)) {
572 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_cheri)) {
573 ArchName = "mips64c128";
574 } else {
575 ArchName = llvm::StringSwitch<const char *>(A->getValue())
576 .Case("64", "mips64c64")
577 .Case("128", "mips64c128")
578 .Case("256", "mips64c256")
579 .Default("mips64c128");
580 }
581 } else if (Arg *A2 = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mcpu_EQ)) {
582 ArchName = llvm::StringSwitch<const char *>(A2->getValue())
583 .Case("cheri64", "mips64c64")
584 .Case("cheri128", "mips64c128")
585 .Case("cheri256", "mips64c256")
586 .Default(nullptr);
587 }
588 // TODO: there is no Triple::setSubArch();
589 if (ArchName)
590 Target.setArchName(ArchName);
591 }
592 }
593 }
594
595 return Target;
596}
597
598// Parse the LTO options and record the type of LTO compilation
599// based on which -f(no-)?lto(=.*)? option occurs last.
600void Driver::setLTOMode(const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args) {
601 LTOMode = LTOK_None;
602 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_flto, options::OPT_flto_EQ,
603 options::OPT_fno_lto, false))
604 return;
605
606 StringRef LTOName("full");
607
608 const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_flto_EQ);
609 if (A)
610 LTOName = A->getValue();
611
612 LTOMode = llvm::StringSwitch<LTOKind>(LTOName)
613 .Case("full", LTOK_Full)
614 .Case("thin", LTOK_Thin)
615 .Default(LTOK_Unknown);
616
617 if (LTOMode == LTOK_Unknown) {
618 assert(A);
619 Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument) << A->getOption().getName()
620 << A->getValue();
621 }
622}
623
624/// Compute the desired OpenMP runtime from the flags provided.
625Driver::OpenMPRuntimeKind Driver::getOpenMPRuntime(const ArgList &Args) const {
626 StringRef RuntimeName(CLANG_DEFAULT_OPENMP_RUNTIME);
627
628 const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_EQ);
629 if (A)
630 RuntimeName = A->getValue();
631
632 auto RT = llvm::StringSwitch<OpenMPRuntimeKind>(RuntimeName)
633 .Case("libomp", OMPRT_OMP)
634 .Case("libgomp", OMPRT_GOMP)
635 .Case("libiomp5", OMPRT_IOMP5)
636 .Default(OMPRT_Unknown);
637
638 if (RT == OMPRT_Unknown) {
639 if (A)
640 Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
641 << A->getOption().getName() << A->getValue();
642 else
643 // FIXME: We could use a nicer diagnostic here.
644 Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt) << "-fopenmp";
645 }
646
647 return RT;
648}
649
650void Driver::CreateOffloadingDeviceToolChains(Compilation &C,
651 InputList &Inputs) {
652
653 //
654 // CUDA/HIP
655 //
656 // We need to generate a CUDA/HIP toolchain if any of the inputs has a CUDA
657 // or HIP type. However, mixed CUDA/HIP compilation is not supported.
658 bool IsCuda =
659 llvm::any_of(Inputs, [](std::pair<types::ID, const llvm::opt::Arg *> &I) {
660 return types::isCuda(I.first);
661 });
662 bool IsHIP =
663 llvm::any_of(Inputs,
664 [](std::pair<types::ID, const llvm::opt::Arg *> &I) {
665 return types::isHIP(I.first);
666 }) ||
667 C.getInputArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_hip_link);
668 if (IsCuda && IsHIP) {
669 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_mix_cuda_hip);
670 return;
671 }
672 if (IsCuda) {
673 const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
674 const llvm::Triple &HostTriple = HostTC->getTriple();
675 StringRef DeviceTripleStr;
676 auto OFK = Action::OFK_Cuda;
677 DeviceTripleStr =
678 HostTriple.isArch64Bit() ? "nvptx64-nvidia-cuda" : "nvptx-nvidia-cuda";
679 llvm::Triple CudaTriple(DeviceTripleStr);
680 // Use the CUDA and host triples as the key into the ToolChains map,
681 // because the device toolchain we create depends on both.
682 auto &CudaTC = ToolChains[CudaTriple.str() + "/" + HostTriple.str()];
683 if (!CudaTC) {
684 CudaTC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
685 *this, CudaTriple, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs(), OFK);
686 }
687 C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(CudaTC.get(), OFK);
688 } else if (IsHIP) {
689 const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
690 const llvm::Triple &HostTriple = HostTC->getTriple();
691 StringRef DeviceTripleStr;
692 auto OFK = Action::OFK_HIP;
693 DeviceTripleStr = "amdgcn-amd-amdhsa";
694 llvm::Triple HIPTriple(DeviceTripleStr);
695 // Use the HIP and host triples as the key into the ToolChains map,
696 // because the device toolchain we create depends on both.
697 auto &HIPTC = ToolChains[HIPTriple.str() + "/" + HostTriple.str()];
698 if (!HIPTC) {
699 HIPTC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::HIPToolChain>(
700 *this, HIPTriple, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs());
701 }
702 C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(HIPTC.get(), OFK);
703 }
704
705 //
706 // OpenMP
707 //
708 // We need to generate an OpenMP toolchain if the user specified targets with
709 // the -fopenmp-targets option.
710 if (Arg *OpenMPTargets =
711 C.getInputArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ)) {
712 if (OpenMPTargets->getNumValues()) {
713 // We expect that -fopenmp-targets is always used in conjunction with the
714 // option -fopenmp specifying a valid runtime with offloading support,
715 // i.e. libomp or libiomp.
716 bool HasValidOpenMPRuntime = C.getInputArgs().hasFlag(
717 options::OPT_fopenmp, options::OPT_fopenmp_EQ,
718 options::OPT_fno_openmp, false);
719 if (HasValidOpenMPRuntime) {
720 OpenMPRuntimeKind OpenMPKind = getOpenMPRuntime(C.getInputArgs());
721 HasValidOpenMPRuntime =
722 OpenMPKind == OMPRT_OMP || OpenMPKind == OMPRT_IOMP5;
723 }
724
725 if (HasValidOpenMPRuntime) {
726 llvm::StringMap<const char *> FoundNormalizedTriples;
727 for (const char *Val : OpenMPTargets->getValues()) {
728 llvm::Triple TT(Val);
729 std::string NormalizedName = TT.normalize();
730
731 // Make sure we don't have a duplicate triple.
732 auto Duplicate = FoundNormalizedTriples.find(NormalizedName);
733 if (Duplicate != FoundNormalizedTriples.end()) {
734 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_omp_offload_target_duplicate)
735 << Val << Duplicate->second;
736 continue;
737 }
738
739 // Store the current triple so that we can check for duplicates in the
740 // following iterations.
741 FoundNormalizedTriples[NormalizedName] = Val;
742
743 // If the specified target is invalid, emit a diagnostic.
744 if (TT.getArch() == llvm::Triple::UnknownArch)
745 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_omp_target) << Val;
746 else {
747 const ToolChain *TC;
748 // CUDA toolchains have to be selected differently. They pair host
749 // and device in their implementation.
750 if (TT.isNVPTX()) {
751 const ToolChain *HostTC =
752 C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
753 assert(HostTC && "Host toolchain should be always defined.");
754 auto &CudaTC =
755 ToolChains[TT.str() + "/" + HostTC->getTriple().normalize()];
756 if (!CudaTC)
757 CudaTC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::CudaToolChain>(
758 *this, TT, *HostTC, C.getInputArgs(), Action::OFK_OpenMP);
759 TC = CudaTC.get();
760 } else
761 TC = &getToolChain(C.getInputArgs(), TT);
762 C.addOffloadDeviceToolChain(TC, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
763 }
764 }
765 } else
766 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_expecting_fopenmp_with_fopenmp_targets);
767 } else
768 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_empty_joined_argument)
769 << OpenMPTargets->getAsString(C.getInputArgs());
770 }
771
772 //
773 // TODO: Add support for other offloading programming models here.
774 //
775}
776
777/// Looks the given directories for the specified file.
778///
779/// \param[out] FilePath File path, if the file was found.
780/// \param[in] Dirs Directories used for the search.
781/// \param[in] FileName Name of the file to search for.
782/// \return True if file was found.
783///
784/// Looks for file specified by FileName sequentially in directories specified
785/// by Dirs.
786///
787static bool searchForFile(SmallVectorImpl<char> &FilePath,
788 ArrayRef<std::string> Dirs,
789 StringRef FileName) {
790 SmallString<128> WPath;
791 for (const StringRef &Dir : Dirs) {
792 if (Dir.empty())
793 continue;
794 WPath.clear();
795 llvm::sys::path::append(WPath, Dir, FileName);
796 llvm::sys::path::native(WPath);
797 if (llvm::sys::fs::is_regular_file(WPath)) {
798 FilePath = std::move(WPath);
799 return true;
800 }
801 }
802 return false;
803}
804
805bool Driver::readConfigFile(StringRef FileName) {
806 // Try reading the given file.
807 SmallVector<const char *, 32> NewCfgArgs;
808 if (!llvm::cl::readConfigFile(FileName, Saver, NewCfgArgs)) {
809 Diag(diag::err_drv_cannot_read_config_file) << FileName;
810 return true;
811 }
812
813 // Read options from config file.
814 llvm::SmallString<128> CfgFileName(FileName);
815 llvm::sys::path::native(CfgFileName);
816 ConfigFile = CfgFileName.str();
817 bool ContainErrors;
818 CfgOptions = llvm::make_unique<InputArgList>(
819 ParseArgStrings(NewCfgArgs, IsCLMode(), ContainErrors));
820 if (ContainErrors) {
821 CfgOptions.reset();
822 return true;
823 }
824
825 if (CfgOptions->hasArg(options::OPT_config)) {
826 CfgOptions.reset();
827 Diag(diag::err_drv_nested_config_file);
828 return true;
829 }
830
831 // Claim all arguments that come from a configuration file so that the driver
832 // does not warn on any that is unused.
833 for (Arg *A : *CfgOptions)
834 A->claim();
835 return false;
836}
837
838bool Driver::loadConfigFile() {
839 std::string CfgFileName;
840 bool FileSpecifiedExplicitly = false;
841
842 // Process options that change search path for config files.
843 if (CLOptions) {
844 if (CLOptions->hasArg(options::OPT_config_system_dir_EQ)) {
845 SmallString<128> CfgDir;
846 CfgDir.append(
847 CLOptions->getLastArgValue(options::OPT_config_system_dir_EQ));
848 if (!CfgDir.empty()) {
849 if (llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(CfgDir).value() != 0)
850 SystemConfigDir.clear();
851 else
852 SystemConfigDir = std::string(CfgDir.begin(), CfgDir.end());
853 }
854 }
855 if (CLOptions->hasArg(options::OPT_config_user_dir_EQ)) {
856 SmallString<128> CfgDir;
857 CfgDir.append(
858 CLOptions->getLastArgValue(options::OPT_config_user_dir_EQ));
859 if (!CfgDir.empty()) {
860 if (llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(CfgDir).value() != 0)
861 UserConfigDir.clear();
862 else
863 UserConfigDir = std::string(CfgDir.begin(), CfgDir.end());
864 }
865 }
866 }
867
868 // First try to find config file specified in command line.
869 if (CLOptions) {
870 std::vector<std::string> ConfigFiles =
871 CLOptions->getAllArgValues(options::OPT_config);
872 if (ConfigFiles.size() > 1) {
873 Diag(diag::err_drv_duplicate_config);
874 return true;
875 }
876
877 if (!ConfigFiles.empty()) {
878 CfgFileName = ConfigFiles.front();
879 assert(!CfgFileName.empty());
880
881 // If argument contains directory separator, treat it as a path to
882 // configuration file.
883 if (llvm::sys::path::has_parent_path(CfgFileName)) {
884 SmallString<128> CfgFilePath;
885 if (llvm::sys::path::is_relative(CfgFileName))
886 llvm::sys::fs::current_path(CfgFilePath);
887 llvm::sys::path::append(CfgFilePath, CfgFileName);
888 if (!llvm::sys::fs::is_regular_file(CfgFilePath)) {
889 Diag(diag::err_drv_config_file_not_exist) << CfgFilePath;
890 return true;
891 }
892 return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath);
893 }
894
895 FileSpecifiedExplicitly = true;
896 }
897 }
898
899 // If config file is not specified explicitly, try to deduce configuration
900 // from executable name. For instance, an executable 'armv7l-clang' will
901 // search for config file 'armv7l-clang.cfg'.
902 if (CfgFileName.empty() && !ClangNameParts.TargetPrefix.empty())
903 CfgFileName = ClangNameParts.TargetPrefix + '-' + ClangNameParts.ModeSuffix;
904
905 if (CfgFileName.empty())
906 return false;
907
908 // Determine architecture part of the file name, if it is present.
909 StringRef CfgFileArch = CfgFileName;
910 size_t ArchPrefixLen = CfgFileArch.find('-');
911 if (ArchPrefixLen == StringRef::npos)
912 ArchPrefixLen = CfgFileArch.size();
913 llvm::Triple CfgTriple;
914 CfgFileArch = CfgFileArch.take_front(ArchPrefixLen);
915 CfgTriple = llvm::Triple(llvm::Triple::normalize(CfgFileArch));
916 if (CfgTriple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::ArchType::UnknownArch)
917 ArchPrefixLen = 0;
918
919 if (!StringRef(CfgFileName).endswith(".cfg"))
920 CfgFileName += ".cfg";
921
922 // If config file starts with architecture name and command line options
923 // redefine architecture (with options like -m32 -LE etc), try finding new
924 // config file with that architecture.
925 SmallString<128> FixedConfigFile;
926 size_t FixedArchPrefixLen = 0;
927 if (ArchPrefixLen) {
928 // Get architecture name from config file name like 'i386.cfg' or
929 // 'armv7l-clang.cfg'.
930 // Check if command line options changes effective triple.
931 llvm::Triple EffectiveTriple = computeTargetTriple(*this,
932 CfgTriple.getTriple(), *CLOptions);
933 if (CfgTriple.getArch() != EffectiveTriple.getArch()) {
934 FixedConfigFile = EffectiveTriple.getArchName();
935 FixedArchPrefixLen = FixedConfigFile.size();
936 // Append the rest of original file name so that file name transforms
937 // like: i386-clang.cfg -> x86_64-clang.cfg.
938 if (ArchPrefixLen < CfgFileName.size())
939 FixedConfigFile += CfgFileName.substr(ArchPrefixLen);
940 }
941 }
942
943 // Prepare list of directories where config file is searched for.
944 SmallVector<std::string, 3> CfgFileSearchDirs;
945 CfgFileSearchDirs.push_back(UserConfigDir);
946 CfgFileSearchDirs.push_back(SystemConfigDir);
947 CfgFileSearchDirs.push_back(Dir);
948
949 // Try to find config file. First try file with corrected architecture.
950 llvm::SmallString<128> CfgFilePath;
951 if (!FixedConfigFile.empty()) {
952 if (searchForFile(CfgFilePath, CfgFileSearchDirs, FixedConfigFile))
953 return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath);
954 // If 'x86_64-clang.cfg' was not found, try 'x86_64.cfg'.
955 FixedConfigFile.resize(FixedArchPrefixLen);
956 FixedConfigFile.append(".cfg");
957 if (searchForFile(CfgFilePath, CfgFileSearchDirs, FixedConfigFile))
958 return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath);
959 }
960
961 // Then try original file name.
962 if (searchForFile(CfgFilePath, CfgFileSearchDirs, CfgFileName))
963 return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath);
964
965 // Finally try removing driver mode part: 'x86_64-clang.cfg' -> 'x86_64.cfg'.
966 if (!ClangNameParts.ModeSuffix.empty() &&
967 !ClangNameParts.TargetPrefix.empty()) {
968 CfgFileName.assign(ClangNameParts.TargetPrefix);
969 CfgFileName.append(".cfg");
970 if (searchForFile(CfgFilePath, CfgFileSearchDirs, CfgFileName))
971 return readConfigFile(CfgFilePath);
972 }
973
974 // Report error but only if config file was specified explicitly, by option
975 // --config. If it was deduced from executable name, it is not an error.
976 if (FileSpecifiedExplicitly) {
977 Diag(diag::err_drv_config_file_not_found) << CfgFileName;
978 for (const std::string &SearchDir : CfgFileSearchDirs)
979 if (!SearchDir.empty())
980 Diag(diag::note_drv_config_file_searched_in) << SearchDir;
981 return true;
982 }
983
984 return false;
985}

987Compilation *Driver::BuildCompilation(ArrayRef<const char *> ArgList) {
988 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Compilation construction");
989
990 // FIXME: Handle environment options which affect driver behavior, somewhere
991 // (client?). GCC_EXEC_PREFIX, LPATH, CC_PRINT_OPTIONS.
992
993 if (Optional<std::string> CompilerPathValue =
994 llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv("COMPILER_PATH")) {
995 StringRef CompilerPath = *CompilerPathValue;
996 while (!CompilerPath.empty()) {
997 std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split =
998 CompilerPath.split(llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator);
999 PrefixDirs.push_back(Split.first);
1000 CompilerPath = Split.second;
1001 }
1002 }
1003
1004 // We look for the driver mode option early, because the mode can affect
1005 // how other options are parsed.
1006 ParseDriverMode(ClangExecutable, ArgList.slice(1));
1007
1008 // FIXME: What are we going to do with -V and -b?
1009
1010 // Arguments specified in command line.
1011 bool ContainsError;
1012 CLOptions = llvm::make_unique<InputArgList>(
1013 ParseArgStrings(ArgList.slice(1), IsCLMode(), ContainsError));
1014
1015 // Try parsing configuration file.
1016 if (!ContainsError)
1017 ContainsError = loadConfigFile();
1018 bool HasConfigFile = !ContainsError && (CfgOptions.get() != nullptr);
1019
1020 // All arguments, from both config file and command line.
1021 InputArgList Args = std::move(HasConfigFile ? std::move(*CfgOptions)
1022 : std::move(*CLOptions));
1023
1024 auto appendOneArg = [&Args](const Arg *Opt, const Arg *BaseArg) {
1025 unsigned Index = Args.MakeIndex(Opt->getSpelling());
1026 Arg *Copy = new llvm::opt::Arg(Opt->getOption(), Opt->getSpelling(),
1027 Index, BaseArg);
1028 Copy->getValues() = Opt->getValues();
1029 if (Opt->isClaimed())
1030 Copy->claim();
1031 Args.append(Copy);
1032 };
1033
1034 if (HasConfigFile)
1035 for (auto *Opt : *CLOptions) {
1036 if (Opt->getOption().matches(options::OPT_config))
1037 continue;
1038 const Arg *BaseArg = &Opt->getBaseArg();
1039 if (BaseArg == Opt)
1040 BaseArg = nullptr;
1041 appendOneArg(Opt, BaseArg);
1042 }
1043
1044 // In CL mode, look for any pass-through arguments
1045 if (IsCLMode() && !ContainsError) {
1046 SmallVector<const char *, 16> CLModePassThroughArgList;
1047 for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT__SLASH_clang)) {
1048 A->claim();
1049 CLModePassThroughArgList.push_back(A->getValue());
1050 }
1051
1052 if (!CLModePassThroughArgList.empty()) {
1053 // Parse any pass through args using default clang processing rather
1054 // than clang-cl processing.
1055 auto CLModePassThroughOptions = llvm::make_unique<InputArgList>(
1056 ParseArgStrings(CLModePassThroughArgList, false, ContainsError));
1057
1058 if (!ContainsError)
1059 for (auto *Opt : *CLModePassThroughOptions) {
1060 appendOneArg(Opt, nullptr);
1061 }
1062 }
1063 }
1064
1065 // Check for working directory option before accessing any files
1066 if (Arg *WD = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_working_directory))
1067 if (VFS->setCurrentWorkingDirectory(WD->getValue()))
1068 Diag(diag::err_drv_unable_to_set_working_directory) << WD->getValue();
1069
1070 // FIXME: This stuff needs to go into the Compilation, not the driver.
1071 bool CCCPrintPhases;
1072
1073 // Silence driver warnings if requested
1074 Diags.setIgnoreAllWarnings(Args.hasArg(options::OPT_w));
1075
1076 // -no-canonical-prefixes is used very early in main.
1077 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_no_canonical_prefixes);
1078
1079 // Ignore -pipe.
1080 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_pipe);
1081
1082 // Extract -ccc args.
1083 //
1084 // FIXME: We need to figure out where this behavior should live. Most of it
1085 // should be outside in the client; the parts that aren't should have proper
1086 // options, either by introducing new ones or by overloading gcc ones like -V
1087 // or -b.
1088 CCCPrintPhases = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ccc_print_phases);
1089 CCCPrintBindings = Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ccc_print_bindings);
1090 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_ccc_gcc_name))
1091 CCCGenericGCCName = A->getValue();
1092 GenReproducer = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_gen_reproducer,
1093 options::OPT_fno_crash_diagnostics,
1094 !!::getenv("FORCE_CLANG_DIAGNOSTICS_CRASH"));
1095 // FIXME: TargetTriple is used by the target-prefixed calls to as/ld
1096 // and getToolChain is const.
1097 if (IsCLMode()) {
1098 // clang-cl targets MSVC-style Win32.
1099 llvm::Triple T(TargetTriple);
1100 T.setOS(llvm::Triple::Win32);
1101 T.setVendor(llvm::Triple::PC);
1102 T.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::MSVC);
1103 T.setObjectFormat(llvm::Triple::COFF);
1104 TargetTriple = T.str();
1105 }
1106 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_target))
1107 TargetTriple = A->getValue();
1108 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_ccc_install_dir))
1109 Dir = InstalledDir = A->getValue();
1110 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_B)) {
1111 A->claim();
1112 PrefixDirs.push_back(A->getValue(0));
1113 }
1114 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__sysroot_EQ))
1115 SysRoot = A->getValue();
1116 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__dyld_prefix_EQ))
1117 DyldPrefix = A->getValue();
1118
1119 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_resource_dir))
1120 ResourceDir = A->getValue();
1121
1122 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_save_temps_EQ)) {
1123 SaveTemps = llvm::StringSwitch<SaveTempsMode>(A->getValue())
1124 .Case("cwd", SaveTempsCwd)
1125 .Case("obj", SaveTempsObj)
1126 .Default(SaveTempsCwd);
1127 }
1128
1129 setLTOMode(Args);
1130
1131 // Process -fembed-bitcode= flags.
1132 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fembed_bitcode_EQ)) {
1133 StringRef Name = A->getValue();
1134 unsigned Model = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
1135 .Case("off", EmbedNone)
1136 .Case("all", EmbedBitcode)
1137 .Case("bitcode", EmbedBitcode)
1138 .Case("marker", EmbedMarker)
1139 .Default(~0U);
1140 if (Model == ~0U) {
1141 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getAsString(Args)
1142 << Name;
1143 } else
1144 BitcodeEmbed = static_cast<BitcodeEmbedMode>(Model);
1145 }
1146
1147 std::unique_ptr<llvm::opt::InputArgList> UArgs =
1148 llvm::make_unique<InputArgList>(std::move(Args));
1149
1150 // Perform the default argument translations.
1151 DerivedArgList *TranslatedArgs = TranslateInputArgs(*UArgs);
1152
1153 // Owned by the host.
1154 const ToolChain &TC = getToolChain(
1155 *UArgs, computeTargetTriple(*this, TargetTriple, *UArgs));
1156
1157 // The compilation takes ownership of Args.
1158 Compilation *C = new Compilation(*this, TC, UArgs.release(), TranslatedArgs,
1159 ContainsError);
1160
1161 if (!HandleImmediateArgs(*C))
1162 return C;
1163
1164 // Construct the list of inputs.
1165 InputList Inputs;
1166 BuildInputs(C->getDefaultToolChain(), *TranslatedArgs, Inputs);
1167
1168 // Populate the tool chains for the offloading devices, if any.
1169 CreateOffloadingDeviceToolChains(*C, Inputs);
1170
1171 // Construct the list of abstract actions to perform for this compilation. On
1172 // MachO targets this uses the driver-driver and universal actions.
1173 if (TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
1174 BuildUniversalActions(*C, C->getDefaultToolChain(), Inputs);
1175 else
1176 BuildActions(*C, C->getArgs(), Inputs, C->getActions());
1177
1178 if (CCCPrintPhases) {
1179 PrintActions(*C);
1180 return C;
1181 }
1182
1183 BuildJobs(*C);
1184
1185 return C;
1186}

1188static void printArgList(raw_ostream &OS, const llvm::opt::ArgList &Args) {
1189 llvm::opt::ArgStringList ASL;
1190 for (const auto *A : Args)
1191 A->render(Args, ASL);
1192
1193 for (auto I = ASL.begin(), E = ASL.end(); I != E; ++I) {
1194 if (I != ASL.begin())
1195 OS << ' ';
1196 Command::printArg(OS, *I, true);
1197 }
1198 OS << '\n';
1199}
1200
1201bool Driver::getCrashDiagnosticFile(StringRef ReproCrashFilename,
1202 SmallString<128> &CrashDiagDir) {
1203 using namespace llvm::sys;
1204 assert(llvm::Triple(llvm::sys::getProcessTriple()).isOSDarwin() &&
1205 "Only knows about .crash files on Darwin");
1206
1207 // The .crash file can be found on at ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/
1208 // (or /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports for root) and has the filename pattern
1209 // clang-<VERSION>_<YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS>_<hostname>.crash.
1210 path::home_directory(CrashDiagDir);
1211 if (CrashDiagDir.startswith("/var/root"))
1212 CrashDiagDir = "/";
1213 path::append(CrashDiagDir, "Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports");
1214 int PID =
1215#if LLVM_ON_UNIX
1216 getpid();
1217#else
1218 0;
1219#endif
1220 std::error_code EC;
1221 fs::file_status FileStatus;
1222 TimePoint<> LastAccessTime;
1223 SmallString<128> CrashFilePath;
1224 // Lookup the .crash files and get the one generated by a subprocess spawned
1225 // by this driver invocation.
1226 for (fs::directory_iterator File(CrashDiagDir, EC), FileEnd;
1227 File != FileEnd && !EC; File.increment(EC)) {
1228 StringRef FileName = path::filename(File->path());
1229 if (!FileName.startswith(Name))
1230 continue;
1231 if (fs::status(File->path(), FileStatus))
1232 continue;
1233 llvm::ErrorOr<std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer>> CrashFile =
1234 llvm::MemoryBuffer::getFile(File->path());
1235 if (!CrashFile)
1236 continue;
1237 // The first line should start with "Process:", otherwise this isn't a real
1238 // .crash file.
1239 StringRef Data = CrashFile.get()->getBuffer();
1240 if (!Data.startswith("Process:"))
1241 continue;
1242 // Parse parent process pid line, e.g: "Parent Process: clang-4.0 [79141]"
1243 size_t ParentProcPos = Data.find("Parent Process:");
1244 if (ParentProcPos == StringRef::npos)
1245 continue;
1246 size_t LineEnd = Data.find_first_of("\n", ParentProcPos);
1247 if (LineEnd == StringRef::npos)
1248 continue;
1249 StringRef ParentProcess = Data.slice(ParentProcPos+15, LineEnd).trim();
1250 int OpenBracket = -1, CloseBracket = -1;
1251 for (size_t i = 0, e = ParentProcess.size(); i < e; ++i) {
1252 if (ParentProcess[i] == '[')
1253 OpenBracket = i;
1254 if (ParentProcess[i] == ']')
1255 CloseBracket = i;
1256 }
1257 // Extract the parent process PID from the .crash file and check whether
1258 // it matches this driver invocation pid.
1259 int CrashPID;
1260 if (OpenBracket < 0 || CloseBracket < 0 ||
1261 ParentProcess.slice(OpenBracket + 1, CloseBracket)
1262 .getAsInteger(10, CrashPID) || CrashPID != PID) {
1263 continue;
1264 }
1265
1266 // Found a .crash file matching the driver pid. To avoid getting an older
1267 // and misleading crash file, continue looking for the most recent.
1268 // FIXME: the driver can dispatch multiple cc1 invocations, leading to
1269 // multiple crashes poiting to the same parent process. Since the driver
1270 // does not collect pid information for the dispatched invocation there's
1271 // currently no way to distinguish among them.
1272 const auto FileAccessTime = FileStatus.getLastModificationTime();
1273 if (FileAccessTime > LastAccessTime) {
1274 CrashFilePath.assign(File->path());
1275 LastAccessTime = FileAccessTime;
1276 }
1277 }
1278
1279 // If found, copy it over to the location of other reproducer files.
1280 if (!CrashFilePath.empty()) {
1281 EC = fs::copy_file(CrashFilePath, ReproCrashFilename);
1282 if (EC)
1283 return false;
1284 return true;
1285 }
1286
1287 return false;
1288}
1289
1290// When clang crashes, produce diagnostic information including the fully
1291// preprocessed source file(s). Request that the developer attach the
1292// diagnostic information to a bug report.
1293void Driver::generateCompilationDiagnostics(
1294 Compilation &C, const Command &FailingCommand,
1295 StringRef AdditionalInformation, CompilationDiagnosticReport *Report) {
1296 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_fno_crash_diagnostics))
1297 return;
1298
1299 // Don't try to generate diagnostics for link or dsymutil jobs.
1300 if (FailingCommand.getCreator().isLinkJob() ||
1301 FailingCommand.getCreator().isDsymutilJob())
1302 return;
1303
1304 // Print the version of the compiler.
1305 PrintVersion(C, llvm::errs());
1306
1307 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1308 << "PLEASE submit a bug report to " BUG_REPORT_URL " and include the "
1309 "crash backtrace, preprocessed source, and associated run script.";
1310
1311 // Suppress driver output and emit preprocessor output to temp file.
1312 Mode = CPPMode;
1313 CCGenDiagnostics = true;
1314
1315 // Save the original job command(s).
1316 Command Cmd = FailingCommand;
1317
1318 // Keep track of whether we produce any errors while trying to produce
1319 // preprocessed sources.
1320 DiagnosticErrorTrap Trap(Diags);
1321
1322 // Suppress tool output.
1323 C.initCompilationForDiagnostics();
1324
1325 // Construct the list of inputs.
1326 InputList Inputs;
1327 BuildInputs(C.getDefaultToolChain(), C.getArgs(), Inputs);
1328
1329 for (InputList::iterator it = Inputs.begin(), ie = Inputs.end(); it != ie;) {
1330 bool IgnoreInput = false;
1331
1332 // Ignore input from stdin or any inputs that cannot be preprocessed.
1333 // Check type first as not all linker inputs have a value.
1334 if (types::getPreprocessedType(it->first) == types::TY_INVALID) {
1335 IgnoreInput = true;
1336 } else if (!strcmp(it->second->getValue(), "-")) {
1337 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1338 << "Error generating preprocessed source(s) - "
1339 "ignoring input from stdin.";
1340 IgnoreInput = true;
1341 }
1342
1343 if (IgnoreInput) {
1344 it = Inputs.erase(it);
1345 ie = Inputs.end();
1346 } else {
1347 ++it;
1348 }
1349 }
1350
1351 if (Inputs.empty()) {
1352 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1353 << "Error generating preprocessed source(s) - "
1354 "no preprocessable inputs.";
1355 return;
1356 }
1357
1358 // Don't attempt to generate preprocessed files if multiple -arch options are
1359 // used, unless they're all duplicates.
1360 llvm::StringSet<> ArchNames;
1361 for (const Arg *A : C.getArgs()) {
1362 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_arch)) {
1363 StringRef ArchName = A->getValue();
1364 ArchNames.insert(ArchName);
1365 }
1366 }
1367 if (ArchNames.size() > 1) {
1368 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1369 << "Error generating preprocessed source(s) - cannot generate "
1370 "preprocessed source with multiple -arch options.";
1371 return;
1372 }
1373
1374 // Construct the list of abstract actions to perform for this compilation. On
1375 // Darwin OSes this uses the driver-driver and builds universal actions.
1376 const ToolChain &TC = C.getDefaultToolChain();
1377 if (TC.getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
1378 BuildUniversalActions(C, TC, Inputs);
1379 else
1380 BuildActions(C, C.getArgs(), Inputs, C.getActions());
1381
1382 BuildJobs(C);
1383
1384 // If there were errors building the compilation, quit now.
1385 if (Trap.hasErrorOccurred()) {
1386 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1387 << "Error generating preprocessed source(s).";
1388 return;
1389 }
1390
1391 // Generate preprocessed output.
1392 SmallVector<std::pair<int, const Command *>, 4> FailingCommands;
1393 C.ExecuteJobs(C.getJobs(), FailingCommands);
1394
1395 // If any of the preprocessing commands failed, clean up and exit.
1396 if (!FailingCommands.empty()) {
1397 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1398 << "Error generating preprocessed source(s).";
1399 return;
1400 }
1401
1402 const ArgStringList &TempFiles = C.getTempFiles();
1403 if (TempFiles.empty()) {
1404 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1405 << "Error generating preprocessed source(s).";
1406 return;
1407 }
1408
1409 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1410 << "\n********************\n\n"
1411 "PLEASE ATTACH THE FOLLOWING FILES TO THE BUG REPORT:\n"
1412 "Preprocessed source(s) and associated run script(s) are located at:";
1413
1414 SmallString<128> VFS;
1415 SmallString<128> ReproCrashFilename;
1416 for (const char *TempFile : TempFiles) {
1417 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << TempFile;
1418 if (Report)
1419 Report->TemporaryFiles.push_back(TempFile);
1420 if (ReproCrashFilename.empty()) {
1421 ReproCrashFilename = TempFile;
1422 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(ReproCrashFilename, ".crash");
1423 }
1424 if (StringRef(TempFile).endswith(".cache")) {
1425 // In some cases (modules) we'll dump extra data to help with reproducing
1426 // the crash into a directory next to the output.
1427 VFS = llvm::sys::path::filename(TempFile);
1428 llvm::sys::path::append(VFS, "vfs", "vfs.yaml");
1429 }
1430 }
1431
1432 // Assume associated files are based off of the first temporary file.
1433 CrashReportInfo CrashInfo(TempFiles[0], VFS);
1434
1435 llvm::SmallString<128> Script(CrashInfo.Filename);
1436 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Script, "sh");
1437 std::error_code EC;
1438 llvm::raw_fd_ostream ScriptOS(Script, EC, llvm::sys::fs::CD_CreateNew);
1439 if (EC) {
1440 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1441 << "Error generating run script: " << Script << " " << EC.message();
1442 } else {
1443 ScriptOS << "# Crash reproducer for " << getClangFullVersion() << "\n"
1444 << "# Driver args: ";
1445 printArgList(ScriptOS, C.getInputArgs());
1446 ScriptOS << "# Original command: ";
1447 Cmd.Print(ScriptOS, "\n", /*Quote=*/true);
1448 Cmd.Print(ScriptOS, "\n", /*Quote=*/true, &CrashInfo);
1449 if (!AdditionalInformation.empty())
1450 ScriptOS << "\n# Additional information: " << AdditionalInformation
1451 << "\n";
1452 if (Report)
1453 Report->TemporaryFiles.push_back(Script.str());
1454 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << Script;
1455 }
1456
1457 // On darwin, provide information about the .crash diagnostic report.
1458 if (llvm::Triple(llvm::sys::getProcessTriple()).isOSDarwin()) {
1459 SmallString<128> CrashDiagDir;
1460 if (getCrashDiagnosticFile(ReproCrashFilename, CrashDiagDir)) {
1461 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1462 << ReproCrashFilename.str();
1463 } else { // Suggest a directory for the user to look for .crash files.
1464 llvm::sys::path::append(CrashDiagDir, Name);
1465 CrashDiagDir += "_<YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS>_<hostname>.crash";
1466 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1467 << "Crash backtrace is located in";
1468 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1469 << CrashDiagDir.str();
1470 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1471 << "(choose the .crash file that corresponds to your crash)";
1472 }
1473 }
1474
1475 for (const auto &A : C.getArgs().filtered(options::OPT_frewrite_map_file,
1476 options::OPT_frewrite_map_file_EQ))
1477 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg) << A->getValue();
1478
1479 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_command_failed_diag_msg)
1480 << "\n\n********************";
1481}
1482
1483void Driver::setUpResponseFiles(Compilation &C, Command &Cmd) {
1484 // Since commandLineFitsWithinSystemLimits() may underestimate system's
1485 // capacity if the tool does not support response files, there is a chance/
1486 // that things will just work without a response file, so we silently just
1487 // skip it.
1488 if (Cmd.getCreator().getResponseFilesSupport() == Tool::RF_None ||
1489 llvm::sys::commandLineFitsWithinSystemLimits(Cmd.getExecutable(),
1490 Cmd.getArguments()))
1491 return;
1492
1493 std::string TmpName = GetTemporaryPath("response", "txt");
1494 Cmd.setResponseFile(C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpName)));
1495}
1496
1497int Driver::ExecuteCompilation(
1498 Compilation &C,
1499 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<int, const Command *>> &FailingCommands) {
1500 // Just print if -### was present.
1501 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH)) {
1502 C.getJobs().Print(llvm::errs(), "\n", true);
1503 return 0;
1504 }
1505
1506 // If there were errors building the compilation, quit now.
1507 if (Diags.hasErrorOccurred())
1508 return 1;
1509
1510 // Set up response file names for each command, if necessary
1511 for (auto &Job : C.getJobs())
1512 setUpResponseFiles(C, Job);
1513
1514 C.ExecuteJobs(C.getJobs(), FailingCommands);
1515
1516 // If the command succeeded, we are done.
1517 if (FailingCommands.empty())
1518 return 0;
1519
1520 // Otherwise, remove result files and print extra information about abnormal
1521 // failures.
1522 int Res = 0;
1523 for (const auto &CmdPair : FailingCommands) {
1524 int CommandRes = CmdPair.first;
1525 const Command *FailingCommand = CmdPair.second;
1526
1527 // Remove result files if we're not saving temps.
1528 if (!isSaveTempsEnabled()) {
1529 const JobAction *JA = cast<JobAction>(&FailingCommand->getSource());
1530 C.CleanupFileMap(C.getResultFiles(), JA, true);
1531
1532 // Failure result files are valid unless we crashed.
1533 if (CommandRes < 0)
1534 C.CleanupFileMap(C.getFailureResultFiles(), JA, true);
1535 }
1536
1537#if LLVM_ON_UNIX
1538 // llvm/lib/Support/Unix/Signals.inc will exit with a special return code
1539 // for SIGPIPE. Do not print diagnostics for this case.
1540 if (CommandRes == EX_IOERR) {
1541 Res = CommandRes;
1542 continue;
1543 }
1544#endif
1545
1546 // Print extra information about abnormal failures, if possible.
1547 //
1548 // This is ad-hoc, but we don't want to be excessively noisy. If the result
1549 // status was 1, assume the command failed normally. In particular, if it
1550 // was the compiler then assume it gave a reasonable error code. Failures
1551 // in other tools are less common, and they generally have worse
1552 // diagnostics, so always print the diagnostic there.
1553 const Tool &FailingTool = FailingCommand->getCreator();
1554
1555 if (!FailingCommand->getCreator().hasGoodDiagnostics() || CommandRes != 1) {
1556 // FIXME: See FIXME above regarding result code interpretation.
1557 if (CommandRes < 0)
1558 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_command_signalled)
1559 << FailingTool.getShortName();
1560 else
1561 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_command_failed)
1562 << FailingTool.getShortName() << CommandRes;
1563 }
1564 }
1565 return Res;
1566}

1568void Driver::PrintHelp(bool ShowHidden) const {
1569 unsigned IncludedFlagsBitmask;
1570 unsigned ExcludedFlagsBitmask;
1571 std::tie(IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask) =
1572 getIncludeExcludeOptionFlagMasks(IsCLMode());
1573
1574 ExcludedFlagsBitmask |= options::NoDriverOption;
1575 if (!ShowHidden)
1576 ExcludedFlagsBitmask |= HelpHidden;
1577
1578 std::string Usage = llvm::formatv("{0} [options] file...", Name).str();
1579 getOpts().PrintHelp(llvm::outs(), Usage.c_str(), DriverTitle.c_str(),
1580 IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask,
1581 /*ShowAllAliases=*/false);
1582}

1584void Driver::PrintVersion(const Compilation &C, raw_ostream &OS) const {
1585 // FIXME: The following handlers should use a callback mechanism, we don't
1586 // know what the client would like to do.
1587 OS << getClangFullVersion() << '\n';
1588 const ToolChain &TC = C.getDefaultToolChain();
1589 OS << "Target: " << TC.getTripleString() << '\n';
1590
1591 // Print the threading model.
1592 if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_mthread_model)) {
1593 // Don't print if the ToolChain would have barfed on it already
1594 if (TC.isThreadModelSupported(A->getValue()))
1595 OS << "Thread model: " << A->getValue();
1596 } else
1597 OS << "Thread model: " << TC.getThreadModel();
1598 OS << '\n';
1599
1600 // Print out the install directory.
1601 OS << "InstalledDir: " << InstalledDir << '\n';
1602
1603 // If configuration file was used, print its path.
1604 if (!ConfigFile.empty())
1605 OS << "Configuration file: " << ConfigFile << '\n';
1606}

1608/// PrintDiagnosticCategories - Implement the --print-diagnostic-categories
1609/// option.
1610static void PrintDiagnosticCategories(raw_ostream &OS) {

1613 ++i)
1614 OS << i << ',' << DiagnosticIDs::getCategoryNameFromID(i) << '\n';

1616
1617void Driver::HandleAutocompletions(StringRef PassedFlags) const {
1618 if (PassedFlags == "")
1619 return;
1620 // Print out all options that start with a given argument. This is used for
1621 // shell autocompletion.
1622 std::vector<std::string> SuggestedCompletions;
1623 std::vector<std::string> Flags;
1624
1625 unsigned short DisableFlags =
1626 options::NoDriverOption | options::Unsupported | options::Ignored;
1627
1628 // Distinguish "--autocomplete=-someflag" and "--autocomplete=-someflag,"
1629 // because the latter indicates that the user put space before pushing tab
1630 // which should end up in a file completion.
1631 const bool HasSpace = PassedFlags.endswith(",");
1632
1633 // Parse PassedFlags by "," as all the command-line flags are passed to this
1634 // function separated by ","
1635 StringRef TargetFlags = PassedFlags;
1636 while (TargetFlags != "") {
1637 StringRef CurFlag;
1638 std::tie(CurFlag, TargetFlags) = TargetFlags.split(",");
1639 Flags.push_back(std::string(CurFlag));
1640 }
1641
1642 // We want to show cc1-only options only when clang is invoked with -cc1 or
1643 // -Xclang.
1644 if (llvm::is_contained(Flags, "-Xclang") || llvm::is_contained(Flags, "-cc1"))
1645 DisableFlags &= ~options::NoDriverOption;
1646
1647 StringRef Cur;
1648 Cur = Flags.at(Flags.size() - 1);
1649 StringRef Prev;
1650 if (Flags.size() >= 2) {
1651 Prev = Flags.at(Flags.size() - 2);
1652 SuggestedCompletions = Opts->suggestValueCompletions(Prev, Cur);
1653 }
1654
1655 if (SuggestedCompletions.empty())
1656 SuggestedCompletions = Opts->suggestValueCompletions(Cur, "");
1657
1658 // If Flags were empty, it means the user typed `clang [tab]` where we should
1659 // list all possible flags. If there was no value completion and the user
1660 // pressed tab after a space, we should fall back to a file completion.
1661 // We're printing a newline to be consistent with what we print at the end of
1662 // this function.
1663 if (SuggestedCompletions.empty() && HasSpace && !Flags.empty()) {
1664 llvm::outs() << '\n';
1665 return;
1666 }
1667
1668 // When flag ends with '=' and there was no value completion, return empty
1669 // string and fall back to the file autocompletion.
1670 if (SuggestedCompletions.empty() && !Cur.endswith("=")) {
1671 // If the flag is in the form of "--autocomplete=-foo",
1672 // we were requested to print out all option names that start with "-foo".
1673 // For example, "--autocomplete=-fsyn" is expanded to "-fsyntax-only".
1674 SuggestedCompletions = Opts->findByPrefix(Cur, DisableFlags);
1675
1676 // We have to query the -W flags manually as they're not in the OptTable.
1677 // TODO: Find a good way to add them to OptTable instead and them remove
1678 // this code.
1679 for (StringRef S : DiagnosticIDs::getDiagnosticFlags())
1680 if (S.startswith(Cur))
1681 SuggestedCompletions.push_back(S);
1682 }
1683
1684 // Sort the autocomplete candidates so that shells print them out in a
1685 // deterministic order. We could sort in any way, but we chose
1686 // case-insensitive sorting for consistency with the -help option
1687 // which prints out options in the case-insensitive alphabetical order.
1688 llvm::sort(SuggestedCompletions, [](StringRef A, StringRef B) {
1689 if (int X = A.compare_lower(B))
1690 return X < 0;
1691 return A.compare(B) > 0;
1692 });
1693
1694 llvm::outs() << llvm::join(SuggestedCompletions, "\n") << '\n';
1695}
1696
1697bool Driver::HandleImmediateArgs(const Compilation &C) {
1698 // The order these options are handled in gcc is all over the place, but we
1699 // don't expect inconsistencies w.r.t. that to matter in practice.
1700
1701 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dumpmachine)) {
1702 llvm::outs() << C.getDefaultToolChain().getTripleString() << '\n';
1703 return false;
1704 }
1705
1706 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_dumpversion)) {
1707 // Since -dumpversion is only implemented for pedantic GCC compatibility, we
1708 // return an answer which matches our definition of __VERSION__.
1709 llvm::outs() << CLANG_VERSION_STRING << "\n";
1710 return false;
1711 }
1712
1713 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__print_diagnostic_categories)) {
1714 PrintDiagnosticCategories(llvm::outs());
1715 return false;
1716 }
1717
1718 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_help) ||
1719 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__help_hidden)) {
1720 PrintHelp(C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__help_hidden));
1721 return false;
1722 }
1723
1724 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__version)) {
1725 // Follow gcc behavior and use stdout for --version and stderr for -v.
1726 PrintVersion(C, llvm::outs());
1727 return false;
1728 }
1729
1730 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v) ||
1731 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH)) {
1732 PrintVersion(C, llvm::errs());
1733 SuppressMissingInputWarning = true;
1734 }
1735
1736 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v)) {
1737 if (!SystemConfigDir.empty())
1738 llvm::errs() << "System configuration file directory: "
1739 << SystemConfigDir << "\n";
1740 if (!UserConfigDir.empty())
1741 llvm::errs() << "User configuration file directory: "
1742 << UserConfigDir << "\n";
1743 }
1744
1745 const ToolChain &TC = C.getDefaultToolChain();
1746
1747 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_v))
1748 TC.printVerboseInfo(llvm::errs());
1749
1750 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_resource_dir)) {
1751 llvm::outs() << ResourceDir << '\n';
1752 return false;
1753 }
1754
1755 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_search_dirs)) {
1756 llvm::outs() << "programs: =";
1757 bool separator = false;
1758 for (const std::string &Path : TC.getProgramPaths()) {
1759 if (separator)
1760 llvm::outs() << llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator;
1761 llvm::outs() << Path;
1762 separator = true;
1763 }
1764 llvm::outs() << "\n";
1765 llvm::outs() << "libraries: =" << ResourceDir;
1766
1767 StringRef sysroot = C.getSysRoot();
1768
1769 for (const std::string &Path : TC.getFilePaths()) {
1770 // Always print a separator. ResourceDir was the first item shown.
1771 llvm::outs() << llvm::sys::EnvPathSeparator;
1772 // Interpretation of leading '=' is needed only for NetBSD.
1773 if (Path[0] == '=')
1774 llvm::outs() << sysroot << Path.substr(1);
1775 else
1776 llvm::outs() << Path;
1777 }
1778 llvm::outs() << "\n";
1779 return false;
1780 }
1781
1782 // FIXME: The following handlers should use a callback mechanism, we don't
1783 // know what the client would like to do.
1784 if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_print_file_name_EQ)) {
1785 llvm::outs() << GetFilePath(A->getValue(), TC) << "\n";
1786 return false;
1787 }
1788
1789 if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_print_prog_name_EQ)) {
1790 StringRef ProgName = A->getValue();
1791
1792 // Null program name cannot have a path.
1793 if (! ProgName.empty())
1794 llvm::outs() << GetProgramPath(ProgName, TC);
1795
1796 llvm::outs() << "\n";
1797 return false;
1798 }
1799
1800 if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_autocomplete)) {
1801 StringRef PassedFlags = A->getValue();
1802 HandleAutocompletions(PassedFlags);
1803 return false;
1804 }
1805
1806 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_libgcc_file_name)) {
1807 ToolChain::RuntimeLibType RLT = TC.GetRuntimeLibType(C.getArgs());
1808 const llvm::Triple Triple(TC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(C.getArgs()));
1809 RegisterEffectiveTriple TripleRAII(TC, Triple);
1810 switch (RLT) {
1811 case ToolChain::RLT_CompilerRT:
1812 llvm::outs() << TC.getCompilerRT(C.getArgs(), "builtins") << "\n";
1813 break;
1814 case ToolChain::RLT_Libgcc:
1815 llvm::outs() << GetFilePath("libgcc.a", TC) << "\n";
1816 break;
1817 }
1818 return false;
1819 }
1820
1821 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_multi_lib)) {
1822 for (const Multilib &Multilib : TC.getMultilibs())
1823 llvm::outs() << Multilib << "\n";
1824 return false;
1825 }
1826
1827 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_multi_directory)) {
1828 const Multilib &Multilib = TC.getMultilib();
1829 if (Multilib.gccSuffix().empty())
1830 llvm::outs() << ".\n";
1831 else {
1832 StringRef Suffix(Multilib.gccSuffix());
1833 assert(Suffix.front() == '/');
1834 llvm::outs() << Suffix.substr(1) << "\n";
1835 }
1836 return false;
1837 }
1838
1839 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_target_triple)) {
1840 llvm::outs() << TC.getTripleString() << "\n";
1841 return false;
1842 }
1843
1844 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_print_effective_triple)) {
1845 const llvm::Triple Triple(TC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(C.getArgs()));
1846 llvm::outs() << Triple.getTriple() << "\n";
1847 return false;
1848 }
1849
1850 return true;
1851}

1853// Display an action graph human-readably. Action A is the "sink" node
1854// and latest-occuring action. Traversal is in pre-order, visiting the
1855// inputs to each action before printing the action itself.
1856static unsigned PrintActions1(const Compilation &C, Action *A,
1857 std::map<Action *, unsigned> &Ids) {
1858 if (Ids.count(A)) // A was already visited.
1859 return Ids[A];
1860
1861 std::string str;
1862 llvm::raw_string_ostream os(str);
1863
1864 os << Action::getClassName(A->getKind()) << ", ";
1865 if (InputAction *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(A)) {
1866 os << "\"" << IA->getInputArg().getValue() << "\"";
1867 } else if (BindArchAction *BIA = dyn_cast<BindArchAction>(A)) {
1868 os << '"' << BIA->getArchName() << '"' << ", {"
1869 << PrintActions1(C, *BIA->input_begin(), Ids) << "}";
1870 } else if (OffloadAction *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(A)) {
1871 bool IsFirst = true;
1872 OA->doOnEachDependence(
1873 [&](Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, const char *BoundArch) {
1874 // E.g. for two CUDA device dependences whose bound arch is sm_20 and
1875 // sm_35 this will generate:
1876 // "cuda-device" (nvptx64-nvidia-cuda:sm_20) {#ID}, "cuda-device"
1877 // (nvptx64-nvidia-cuda:sm_35) {#ID}
1878 if (!IsFirst)
1879 os << ", ";
1880 os << '"';
1881 if (TC)
1882 os << A->getOffloadingKindPrefix();
1883 else
1884 os << "host";
1885 os << " (";
1886 os << TC->getTriple().normalize();
1887
1888 if (BoundArch)
1889 os << ":" << BoundArch;
1890 os << ")";
1891 os << '"';
1892 os << " {" << PrintActions1(C, A, Ids) << "}";
1893 IsFirst = false;
1894 });
1895 } else {
1896 const ActionList *AL = &A->getInputs();
1897
1898 if (AL->size()) {
1899 const char *Prefix = "{";
1900 for (Action *PreRequisite : *AL) {
1901 os << Prefix << PrintActions1(C, PreRequisite, Ids);
1902 Prefix = ", ";
1903 }
1904 os << "}";
1905 } else
1906 os << "{}";
1907 }
1908
1909 // Append offload info for all options other than the offloading action
1910 // itself (e.g. (cuda-device, sm_20) or (cuda-host)).
1911 std::string offload_str;
1912 llvm::raw_string_ostream offload_os(offload_str);
1913 if (!isa<OffloadAction>(A)) {
1914 auto S = A->getOffloadingKindPrefix();
1915 if (!S.empty()) {
1916 offload_os << ", (" << S;
1917 if (A->getOffloadingArch())
1918 offload_os << ", " << A->getOffloadingArch();
1919 offload_os << ")";
1920 }
1921 }
1922
1923 unsigned Id = Ids.size();
1924 Ids[A] = Id;
1925 llvm::errs() << Id << ": " << os.str() << ", "
1926 << types::getTypeName(A->getType()) << offload_os.str() << "\n";
1927
1928 return Id;
1929}

1932// For example "clang -c file1.c file2.c" is composed of two subgraphs.
1933void Driver::PrintActions(const Compilation &C) const {
1934 std::map<Action *, unsigned> Ids;
1935 for (Action *A : C.getActions())
1936 PrintActions1(C, A, Ids);

1939/// Check whether the given input tree contains any compilation or
1940/// assembly actions.
1941static bool ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction(const Action *A) {
1942 if (isa<CompileJobAction>(A) || isa<BackendJobAction>(A) ||
1943 isa<AssembleJobAction>(A))
1944 return true;
1945
1946 for (const Action *Input : A->inputs())
1947 if (ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction(Input))
1948 return true;
1949
1950 return false;
1951}

1953void Driver::BuildUniversalActions(Compilation &C, const ToolChain &TC,
1954 const InputList &BAInputs) const {
1955 DerivedArgList &Args = C.getArgs();
1956 ActionList &Actions = C.getActions();
1957 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building universal build actions");
1958 // Collect the list of architectures. Duplicates are allowed, but should only
1959 // be handled once (in the order seen).
1960 llvm::StringSet<> ArchNames;
1961 SmallVector<const char *, 4> Archs;
1962 for (Arg *A : Args) {
1963 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_arch)) {
1964 // Validate the option here; we don't save the type here because its
1965 // particular spelling may participate in other driver choices.
1966 llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch =
1967 tools::darwin::getArchTypeForMachOArchName(A->getValue());
1968 if (Arch == llvm::Triple::UnknownArch) {
1969 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_arch_name) << A->getAsString(Args);
1970 continue;
1971 }
1972
1973 A->claim();
1974 if (ArchNames.insert(A->getValue()).second)
1975 Archs.push_back(A->getValue());
1976 }
1977 }
1978
1979 // When there is no explicit arch for this platform, make sure we still bind
1980 // the architecture (to the default) so that -Xarch_ is handled correctly.
1981 if (!Archs.size())
1982 Archs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TC.getDefaultUniversalArchName()));
1983
1984 ActionList SingleActions;
1985 BuildActions(C, Args, BAInputs, SingleActions);
1986
1987 // Add in arch bindings for every top level action, as well as lipo and
1988 // dsymutil steps if needed.
1989 for (Action* Act : SingleActions) {
1990 // Make sure we can lipo this kind of output. If not (and it is an actual
1991 // output) then we disallow, since we can't create an output file with the
1992 // right name without overwriting it. We could remove this oddity by just
1993 // changing the output names to include the arch, which would also fix
1994 // -save-temps. Compatibility wins for now.
1995
1996 if (Archs.size() > 1 && !types::canLipoType(Act->getType()))
1997 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_output_with_multiple_archs)
1998 << types::getTypeName(Act->getType());
1999
2000 ActionList Inputs;
2001 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Archs.size(); i != e; ++i)
2002 Inputs.push_back(C.MakeAction<BindArchAction>(Act, Archs[i]));
2003
2004 // Lipo if necessary, we do it this way because we need to set the arch flag
2005 // so that -Xarch_ gets overwritten.
2006 if (Inputs.size() == 1 || Act->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
2007 Actions.append(Inputs.begin(), Inputs.end());
2008 else
2009 Actions.push_back(C.MakeAction<LipoJobAction>(Inputs, Act->getType()));
2010
2011 // Handle debug info queries.
2012 Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_g_Group);
2013 if (A && !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_g0) &&
2014 !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gstabs) &&
2015 ContainsCompileOrAssembleAction(Actions.back())) {
2016
2017 // Add a 'dsymutil' step if necessary, when debug info is enabled and we
2018 // have a compile input. We need to run 'dsymutil' ourselves in such cases
2019 // because the debug info will refer to a temporary object file which
2020 // will be removed at the end of the compilation process.
2021 if (Act->getType() == types::TY_Image) {
2022 ActionList Inputs;
2023 Inputs.push_back(Actions.back());
2024 Actions.pop_back();
2025 Actions.push_back(
2026 C.MakeAction<DsymutilJobAction>(Inputs, types::TY_dSYM));
2027 }
2028
2029 // Verify the debug info output.
2030 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_verify_debug_info)) {
2031 Action* LastAction = Actions.back();
2032 Actions.pop_back();
2033 Actions.push_back(C.MakeAction<VerifyDebugInfoJobAction>(
2034 LastAction, types::TY_Nothing));
2035 }
2036 }
2037 }
2038}

2040bool Driver::DiagnoseInputExistence(const DerivedArgList &Args, StringRef Value,
2041 types::ID Ty, bool TypoCorrect) const {
2042 if (!getCheckInputsExist())
2043 return true;
2044
2045 // stdin always exists.
2046 if (Value == "-")
2047 return true;
2048
2049 if (getVFS().exists(Value))
2050 return true;
2051
2052 if (IsCLMode()) {
2053 if (!llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(Twine(Value)) &&
2054 llvm::sys::Process::FindInEnvPath("LIB", Value))
2055 return true;
2056
2057 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_link) && Ty == types::TY_Object) {
2058 // Arguments to the /link flag might cause the linker to search for object
2059 // and library files in paths we don't know about. Don't error in such
2060 // cases.
2061 return true;
2062 }
2063 }
2064
2065 if (TypoCorrect) {
2066 // Check if the filename is a typo for an option flag. OptTable thinks
2067 // that all args that are not known options and that start with / are
2068 // filenames, but e.g. `/diagnostic:caret` is more likely a typo for
2069 // the option `/diagnostics:caret` than a reference to a file in the root
2070 // directory.
2071 unsigned IncludedFlagsBitmask;
2072 unsigned ExcludedFlagsBitmask;
2073 std::tie(IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask) =
2074 getIncludeExcludeOptionFlagMasks(IsCLMode());
2075 std::string Nearest;
2076 if (getOpts().findNearest(Value, Nearest, IncludedFlagsBitmask,
2077 ExcludedFlagsBitmask) <= 1) {
2078 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_no_such_file_with_suggestion)
2079 << Value << Nearest;
2080 return false;
2081 }
2082 }
2083
2084 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_no_such_file) << Value;
2085 return false;
2086}
