2088// Construct a the list of inputs and their types.
2089void Driver::BuildInputs(const ToolChain &TC, DerivedArgList &Args,
2090 InputList &Inputs) const {
2091 // Track the current user specified (-x) input. We also explicitly track the
2092 // argument used to set the type; we only want to claim the type when we
2093 // actually use it, so we warn about unused -x arguments.
2094 types::ID InputType = types::TY_Nothing;
2095 Arg *InputTypeArg = nullptr;
2096
2097 // The last /TC or /TP option sets the input type to C or C++ globally.
2098 if (Arg *TCTP = Args.getLastArgNoClaim(options::OPT__SLASH_TC,
2099 options::OPT__SLASH_TP)) {
2100 InputTypeArg = TCTP;
2101 InputType = TCTP->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_TC)
2102 ? types::TY_C
2103 : types::TY_CXX;
2104
2105 Arg *Previous = nullptr;
2106 bool ShowNote = false;
2107 for (Arg *A :
2108 Args.filtered(options::OPT__SLASH_TC, options::OPT__SLASH_TP)) {
2109 if (Previous) {
2110 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_overriding_flag_option)
2111 << Previous->getSpelling() << A->getSpelling();
2112 ShowNote = true;
2113 }
2114 Previous = A;
2115 }
2116 if (ShowNote)
2117 Diag(clang::diag::note_drv_t_option_is_global);
2118
2119 // No driver mode exposes -x and /TC or /TP; we don't support mixing them.
2120 assert(!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_x) && "-x and /TC or /TP is not allowed");
2121 }
2122
2123 for (Arg *A : Args) {
2124 if (A->getOption().getKind() == Option::InputClass) {
2125 const char *Value = A->getValue();
2126 types::ID Ty = types::TY_INVALID;
2127
2128 // Infer the input type if necessary.
2129 if (InputType == types::TY_Nothing) {
2130 // If there was an explicit arg for this, claim it.
2131 if (InputTypeArg)
2132 InputTypeArg->claim();
2133
2134 // stdin must be handled specially.
2135 if (memcmp(Value, "-", 2) == 0) {
2136 // If running with -E, treat as a C input (this changes the builtin
2137 // macros, for example). This may be overridden by -ObjC below.
2138 //
2139 // Otherwise emit an error but still use a valid type to avoid
2140 // spurious errors (e.g., no inputs).
2141 if (!Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_E) && !CCCIsCPP())
2142 Diag(IsCLMode() ? clang::diag::err_drv_unknown_stdin_type_clang_cl
2143 : clang::diag::err_drv_unknown_stdin_type);
2144 Ty = types::TY_C;
2145 } else {
2146 // Otherwise lookup by extension.
2147 // Fallback is C if invoked as C preprocessor, C++ if invoked with
2148 // clang-cl /E, or Object otherwise.
2149 // We use a host hook here because Darwin at least has its own
2150 // idea of what .s is.
2151 if (const char *Ext = strrchr(Value, '.'))
2152 Ty = TC.LookupTypeForExtension(Ext + 1);
2153
2154 if (Ty == types::TY_INVALID) {
2155 if (CCCIsCPP())
2156 Ty = types::TY_C;
2157 else if (IsCLMode() && Args.hasArgNoClaim(options::OPT_E))
2158 Ty = types::TY_CXX;
2159 else
2160 Ty = types::TY_Object;
2161 }
2162
2163 // If the driver is invoked as C++ compiler (like clang++ or c++) it
2164 // should autodetect some input files as C++ for g++ compatibility.
2165 if (CCCIsCXX()) {
2166 types::ID OldTy = Ty;
2167 Ty = types::lookupCXXTypeForCType(Ty);
2168
2169 if (Ty != OldTy)
2170 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_treating_input_as_cxx)
2171 << getTypeName(OldTy) << getTypeName(Ty);
2172 }
2173 }
2174
2175 // -ObjC and -ObjC++ override the default language, but only for "source
2176 // files". We just treat everything that isn't a linker input as a
2177 // source file.
2178 //
2179 // FIXME: Clean this up if we move the phase sequence into the type.
2180 if (Ty != types::TY_Object) {
2181 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ObjC))
2182 Ty = types::TY_ObjC;
2183 else if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ObjCXX))
2184 Ty = types::TY_ObjCXX;
2185 }
2186 } else {
2187 assert(InputTypeArg && "InputType set w/o InputTypeArg");
2188 if (!InputTypeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_x)) {
2189 // If emulating cl.exe, make sure that /TC and /TP don't affect input
2190 // object files.
2191 const char *Ext = strrchr(Value, '.');
2192 if (Ext && TC.LookupTypeForExtension(Ext + 1) == types::TY_Object)
2193 Ty = types::TY_Object;
2194 }
2195 if (Ty == types::TY_INVALID) {
2196 Ty = InputType;
2197 InputTypeArg->claim();
2198 }
2199 }
2200
2201 if (DiagnoseInputExistence(Args, Value, Ty, /*TypoCorrect=*/true))
2202 Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(Ty, A));
2203
2204 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_Tc)) {
2205 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
2206 if (DiagnoseInputExistence(Args, Value, types::TY_C,
2207 /*TypoCorrect=*/false)) {
2208 Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, *Opts, A->getValue());
2209 Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_C, InputArg));
2210 }
2211 A->claim();
2212 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_Tp)) {
2213 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
2214 if (DiagnoseInputExistence(Args, Value, types::TY_CXX,
2215 /*TypoCorrect=*/false)) {
2216 Arg *InputArg = MakeInputArg(Args, *Opts, A->getValue());
2217 Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_CXX, InputArg));
2218 }
2219 A->claim();
2220 } else if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::LinkerInput)) {
2221 // Just treat as object type, we could make a special type for this if
2222 // necessary.
2223 Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_Object, A));
2224
2225 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_x)) {
2226 InputTypeArg = A;
2227 InputType = types::lookupTypeForTypeSpecifier(A->getValue());
2228 A->claim();
2229
2230 // Follow gcc behavior and treat as linker input for invalid -x
2231 // options. Its not clear why we shouldn't just revert to unknown; but
2232 // this isn't very important, we might as well be bug compatible.
2233 if (!InputType) {
2234 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_unknown_language) << A->getValue();
2235 InputType = types::TY_Object;
2236 }
2237 } else if (A->getOption().getID() == options::OPT__SLASH_U) {
2238 assert(A->getNumValues() == 1 && "The /U option has one value.");
2239 StringRef Val = A->getValue(0);
2240 if (Val.find_first_of("/\\") != StringRef::npos) {
2241 // Warn about e.g. "/Users/me/myfile.c".
2242 Diag(diag::warn_slash_u_filename) << Val;
2243 Diag(diag::note_use_dashdash);
2244 }
2245 }
2246 }
2247 if (CCCIsCPP() && Inputs.empty()) {
2248 // If called as standalone preprocessor, stdin is processed
2249 // if no other input is present.
2250 Arg *A = MakeInputArg(Args, *Opts, "-");
2251 Inputs.push_back(std::make_pair(types::TY_C, A));
2252 }
2253}

2349 /// Base class for CUDA/HIP action builder. It injects device code in
2350 /// the host backend action.
2351 class CudaActionBuilderBase : public DeviceActionBuilder {
2352 protected:
2353 /// Flags to signal if the user requested host-only or device-only
2354 /// compilation.
2355 bool CompileHostOnly = false;
2356 bool CompileDeviceOnly = false;
2357
2358 /// List of GPU architectures to use in this compilation.
2359 SmallVector<CudaArch, 4> GpuArchList;
2360
2361 /// The CUDA actions for the current input.
2362 ActionList CudaDeviceActions;
2363
2364 /// The CUDA fat binary if it was generated for the current input.
2365 Action *CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
2366
2367 /// Flag that is set to true if this builder acted on the current input.
2368 bool IsActive = false;
2369
2370 /// Flag for -fgpu-rdc.
2371 bool Relocatable = false;
2372 public:
2373 CudaActionBuilderBase(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
2374 const Driver::InputList &Inputs,
2375 Action::OffloadKind OFKind)
2376 : DeviceActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, OFKind) {}
2377
2378 ActionBuilderReturnCode addDeviceDepences(Action *HostAction) override {
2379 // While generating code for CUDA, we only depend on the host input action
2380 // to trigger the creation of all the CUDA device actions.
2381
2382 // If we are dealing with an input action, replicate it for each GPU
2383 // architecture. If we are in host-only mode we return 'success' so that
2384 // the host uses the CUDA offload kind.
2385 if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(HostAction)) {
2386 assert(!GpuArchList.empty() &&
2387 "We should have at least one GPU architecture.");
2388
2389 // If the host input is not CUDA or HIP, we don't need to bother about
2390 // this input.
2391 if (IA->getType() != types::TY_CUDA &&
2392 IA->getType() != types::TY_HIP) {
2393 // The builder will ignore this input.
2394 IsActive = false;
2395 return ABRT_Inactive;
2396 }
2397
2398 // Set the flag to true, so that the builder acts on the current input.
2399 IsActive = true;
2400
2401 if (CompileHostOnly)
2402 return ABRT_Success;
2403
2404 // Replicate inputs for each GPU architecture.
2405 auto Ty = IA->getType() == types::TY_HIP ? types::TY_HIP_DEVICE
2406 : types::TY_CUDA_DEVICE;
2407 for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
2408 CudaDeviceActions.push_back(
2409 C.MakeAction<InputAction>(IA->getInputArg(), Ty));
2410 }
2411
2412 return ABRT_Success;
2413 }
2414
2415 // If this is an unbundling action use it as is for each CUDA toolchain.
2416 if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction)) {
2417
2418 // If -fgpu-rdc is disabled, should not unbundle since there is no
2419 // device code to link.
2420 if (!Relocatable)
2421 return ABRT_Inactive;
2422
2423 CudaDeviceActions.clear();
2424 auto *IA = cast<InputAction>(UA->getInputs().back());
2425 std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
2426 // Check if the type of the file is the same as the action. Do not
2427 // unbundle it if it is not. Do not unbundle .so files, for example,
2428 // which are not object files.
2429 if (IA->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
2430 (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(FileName) ||
2431 types::lookupTypeForExtension(
2432 llvm::sys::path::extension(FileName).drop_front()) !=
2433 types::TY_Object))
2434 return ABRT_Inactive;
2435
2436 for (auto Arch : GpuArchList) {
2437 CudaDeviceActions.push_back(UA);
2438 UA->registerDependentActionInfo(ToolChains[0], CudaArchToString(Arch),
2439 AssociatedOffloadKind);
2440 }
2441 return ABRT_Success;
2442 }
2443
2444 return IsActive ? ABRT_Success : ABRT_Inactive;
2445 }
2446
2447 void appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL) override {
2448 // Utility to append actions to the top level list.
2449 auto AddTopLevel = [&](Action *A, CudaArch BoundArch) {
2450 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
2451 Dep.add(*A, *ToolChains.front(), CudaArchToString(BoundArch),
2452 AssociatedOffloadKind);
2453 AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, A->getType()));
2454 };
2455
2456 // If we have a fat binary, add it to the list.
2457 if (CudaFatBinary) {
2458 AddTopLevel(CudaFatBinary, CudaArch::UNKNOWN);
2459 CudaDeviceActions.clear();
2460 CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
2461 return;
2462 }
2463
2464 if (CudaDeviceActions.empty())
2465 return;
2466
2467 // If we have CUDA actions at this point, that's because we have a have
2468 // partial compilation, so we should have an action for each GPU
2469 // architecture.
2470 assert(CudaDeviceActions.size() == GpuArchList.size() &&
2471 "Expecting one action per GPU architecture.");
2472 assert(ToolChains.size() == 1 &&
2473 "Expecting to have a sing CUDA toolchain.");
2474 for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I)
2475 AddTopLevel(CudaDeviceActions[I], GpuArchList[I]);
2476
2477 CudaDeviceActions.clear();
2478 }
2479
2480 bool initialize() override {
2481 assert(AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Cuda ||
2482 AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP);
2483
2484 // We don't need to support CUDA.
2485 if (AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Cuda &&
2486 !C.hasOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>())
2487 return false;
2488
2489 // We don't need to support HIP.
2490 if (AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP &&
2491 !C.hasOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>())
2492 return false;
2493
2494 Relocatable = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fgpu_rdc,
2495 options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, /*Default=*/false);
2496
2497 const ToolChain *HostTC = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>();
2498 assert(HostTC && "No toolchain for host compilation.");
2499 if (HostTC->getTriple().isNVPTX() ||
2500 HostTC->getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::amdgcn) {
2501 // We do not support targeting NVPTX/AMDGCN for host compilation. Throw
2502 // an error and abort pipeline construction early so we don't trip
2503 // asserts that assume device-side compilation.
2504 C.getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_cuda_host_arch)
2505 << HostTC->getTriple().getArchName();
2506 return true;
2507 }
2508
2509 ToolChains.push_back(
2510 AssociatedOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Cuda
2511 ? C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>()
2512 : C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>());
2513
2514 Arg *PartialCompilationArg = Args.getLastArg(
2515 options::OPT_cuda_host_only, options::OPT_cuda_device_only,
2516 options::OPT_cuda_compile_host_device);
2517 CompileHostOnly = PartialCompilationArg &&
2518 PartialCompilationArg->getOption().matches(
2519 options::OPT_cuda_host_only);
2520 CompileDeviceOnly = PartialCompilationArg &&
2521 PartialCompilationArg->getOption().matches(
2522 options::OPT_cuda_device_only);
2523
2524 // Collect all cuda_gpu_arch parameters, removing duplicates.
2525 std::set<CudaArch> GpuArchs;
2526 bool Error = false;
2527 for (Arg *A : Args) {
2528 if (!(A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_cuda_gpu_arch_EQ) ||
2529 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_cuda_gpu_arch_EQ)))
2530 continue;
2531 A->claim();
2532
2533 const StringRef ArchStr = A->getValue();
2534 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_cuda_gpu_arch_EQ) &&
2535 ArchStr == "all") {
2536 GpuArchs.clear();
2537 continue;
2538 }
2539 CudaArch Arch = StringToCudaArch(ArchStr);
2540 if (Arch == CudaArch::UNKNOWN) {
2541 C.getDriver().Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_cuda_bad_gpu_arch) << ArchStr;
2542 Error = true;
2543 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_cuda_gpu_arch_EQ))
2544 GpuArchs.insert(Arch);
2545 else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_no_cuda_gpu_arch_EQ))
2546 GpuArchs.erase(Arch);
2547 else
2548 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected option.");
2549 }
2550
2551 // Collect list of GPUs remaining in the set.
2552 for (CudaArch Arch : GpuArchs)
2553 GpuArchList.push_back(Arch);
2554
2555 // Default to sm_20 which is the lowest common denominator for
2556 // supported GPUs. sm_20 code should work correctly, if
2557 // suboptimally, on all newer GPUs.
2558 if (GpuArchList.empty())
2559 GpuArchList.push_back(CudaArch::SM_20);
2560
2561 return Error;
2562 }
2563 };
2564
2565 /// \brief CUDA action builder. It injects device code in the host backend
2566 /// action.
2567 class CudaActionBuilder final : public CudaActionBuilderBase {
2568 public:
2569 CudaActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
2570 const Driver::InputList &Inputs)
2571 : CudaActionBuilderBase(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_Cuda) {}
2572
2573 ActionBuilderReturnCode
2574 getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
2575 phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
2576 PhasesTy &Phases) override {
2577 if (!IsActive)
2578 return ABRT_Inactive;
2579
2580 // If we don't have more CUDA actions, we don't have any dependences to
2581 // create for the host.
2582 if (CudaDeviceActions.empty())
2583 return ABRT_Success;
2584
2585 assert(CudaDeviceActions.size() == GpuArchList.size() &&
2586 "Expecting one action per GPU architecture.");
2587 assert(!CompileHostOnly &&
2588 "Not expecting CUDA actions in host-only compilation.");
2589
2590 // If we are generating code for the device or we are in a backend phase,
2591 // we attempt to generate the fat binary. We compile each arch to ptx and
2592 // assemble to cubin, then feed the cubin *and* the ptx into a device
2593 // "link" action, which uses fatbinary to combine these cubins into one
2594 // fatbin. The fatbin is then an input to the host action if not in
2595 // device-only mode.
2596 if (CompileDeviceOnly || CurPhase == phases::Backend) {
2597 ActionList DeviceActions;
2598 for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
2599 // Produce the device action from the current phase up to the assemble
2600 // phase.
2601 for (auto Ph : Phases) {
2602 // Skip the phases that were already dealt with.
2603 if (Ph < CurPhase)
2604 continue;
2605 // We have to be consistent with the host final phase.
2606 if (Ph > FinalPhase)
2607 break;
2608
2609 CudaDeviceActions[I] = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(
2610 C, Args, Ph, CudaDeviceActions[I], Action::OFK_Cuda);
2611
2612 if (Ph == phases::Assemble)
2613 break;
2614 }
2615
2616 // If we didn't reach the assemble phase, we can't generate the fat
2617 // binary. We don't need to generate the fat binary if we are not in
2618 // device-only mode.
2619 if (!isa<AssembleJobAction>(CudaDeviceActions[I]) ||
2620 CompileDeviceOnly)
2621 continue;
2622
2623 Action *AssembleAction = CudaDeviceActions[I];
2624 assert(AssembleAction->getType() == types::TY_Object);
2625 assert(AssembleAction->getInputs().size() == 1);
2626
2627 Action *BackendAction = AssembleAction->getInputs()[0];
2628 assert(BackendAction->getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm);
2629
2630 for (auto &A : {AssembleAction, BackendAction}) {
2631 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
2632 DDep.add(*A, *ToolChains.front(), CudaArchToString(GpuArchList[I]),
2633 Action::OFK_Cuda);
2634 DeviceActions.push_back(
2635 C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(DDep, A->getType()));
2636 }
2637 }
2638
2639 // We generate the fat binary if we have device input actions.
2640 if (!DeviceActions.empty()) {
2641 CudaFatBinary =
2642 C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(DeviceActions, types::TY_CUDA_FATBIN);
2643
2644 if (!CompileDeviceOnly) {
2645 DA.add(*CudaFatBinary, *ToolChains.front(), /*BoundArch=*/nullptr,
2646 Action::OFK_Cuda);
2647 // Clear the fat binary, it is already a dependence to an host
2648 // action.
2649 CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
2650 }
2651
2652 // Remove the CUDA actions as they are already connected to an host
2653 // action or fat binary.
2654 CudaDeviceActions.clear();
2655 }
2656
2657 // We avoid creating host action in device-only mode.
2658 return CompileDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
2659 } else if (CurPhase > phases::Backend) {
2660 // If we are past the backend phase and still have a device action, we
2661 // don't have to do anything as this action is already a device
2662 // top-level action.
2663 return ABRT_Success;
2664 }
2665
2666 assert(CurPhase < phases::Backend && "Generating single CUDA "
2667 "instructions should only occur "
2668 "before the backend phase!");
2669
2670 // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
2671 for (Action *&A : CudaDeviceActions)
2672 A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A);
2673
2674 return ABRT_Success;
2675 }
2676 };
2677 /// \brief HIP action builder. It injects device code in the host backend
2678 /// action.
2679 class HIPActionBuilder final : public CudaActionBuilderBase {
2680 /// The linker inputs obtained for each device arch.
2681 SmallVector<ActionList, 8> DeviceLinkerInputs;
2682
2683 public:
2684 HIPActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
2685 const Driver::InputList &Inputs)
2686 : CudaActionBuilderBase(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_HIP) {}
2687
2688 bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const override { return true; }
2689
2690 ActionBuilderReturnCode
2691 getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
2692 phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
2693 PhasesTy &Phases) override {
2694 // amdgcn does not support linking of object files, therefore we skip
2695 // backend and assemble phases to output LLVM IR. Except for generating
2696 // non-relocatable device coee, where we generate fat binary for device
2697 // code and pass to host in Backend phase.
2698 if (CudaDeviceActions.empty() ||
2699 (CurPhase == phases::Backend && Relocatable) ||
2700 CurPhase == phases::Assemble)
2701 return ABRT_Success;
2702
2703 assert(((CurPhase == phases::Link && Relocatable) ||
2704 CudaDeviceActions.size() == GpuArchList.size()) &&
2705 "Expecting one action per GPU architecture.");
2706 assert(!CompileHostOnly &&
2707 "Not expecting CUDA actions in host-only compilation.");
2708
2709 if (!Relocatable && CurPhase == phases::Backend) {
2710 // If we are in backend phase, we attempt to generate the fat binary.
2711 // We compile each arch to IR and use a link action to generate code
2712 // object containing ISA. Then we use a special "link" action to create
2713 // a fat binary containing all the code objects for different GPU's.
2714 // The fat binary is then an input to the host action.
2715 for (unsigned I = 0, E = GpuArchList.size(); I != E; ++I) {
2716 // Create a link action to link device IR with device library
2717 // and generate ISA.
2718 ActionList AL;
2719 AL.push_back(CudaDeviceActions[I]);
2720 CudaDeviceActions[I] =
2721 C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(AL, types::TY_Image);
2722
2723 // OffloadingActionBuilder propagates device arch until an offload
2724 // action. Since the next action for creating fatbin does
2725 // not have device arch, whereas the above link action and its input
2726 // have device arch, an offload action is needed to stop the null
2727 // device arch of the next action being propagated to the above link
2728 // action.
2729 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
2730 DDep.add(*CudaDeviceActions[I], *ToolChains.front(),
2731 CudaArchToString(GpuArchList[I]), AssociatedOffloadKind);
2732 CudaDeviceActions[I] = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(
2733 DDep, CudaDeviceActions[I]->getType());
2734 }
2735 // Create HIP fat binary with a special "link" action.
2736 CudaFatBinary =
2737 C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(CudaDeviceActions,
2738 types::TY_HIP_FATBIN);
2739
2740 if (!CompileDeviceOnly) {
2741 DA.add(*CudaFatBinary, *ToolChains.front(), /*BoundArch=*/nullptr,
2742 AssociatedOffloadKind);
2743 // Clear the fat binary, it is already a dependence to an host
2744 // action.
2745 CudaFatBinary = nullptr;
2746 }
2747
2748 // Remove the CUDA actions as they are already connected to an host
2749 // action or fat binary.
2750 CudaDeviceActions.clear();
2751
2752 return CompileDeviceOnly ? ABRT_Ignore_Host : ABRT_Success;
2753 } else if (CurPhase == phases::Link) {
2754 // Save CudaDeviceActions to DeviceLinkerInputs for each GPU subarch.
2755 // This happens to each device action originated from each input file.
2756 // Later on, device actions in DeviceLinkerInputs are used to create
2757 // device link actions in appendLinkDependences and the created device
2758 // link actions are passed to the offload action as device dependence.
2759 DeviceLinkerInputs.resize(CudaDeviceActions.size());
2760 auto LI = DeviceLinkerInputs.begin();
2761 for (auto *A : CudaDeviceActions) {
2762 LI->push_back(A);
2763 ++LI;
2764 }
2765
2766 // We will pass the device action as a host dependence, so we don't
2767 // need to do anything else with them.
2768 CudaDeviceActions.clear();
2769 return ABRT_Success;
2770 }
2771
2772 // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
2773 for (Action *&A : CudaDeviceActions)
2774 A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A,
2775 AssociatedOffloadKind);
2776
2777 return ABRT_Success;
2778 }
2779
2780 void appendLinkDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA) override {
2781 // Append a new link action for each device.
2782 unsigned I = 0;
2783 for (auto &LI : DeviceLinkerInputs) {
2784 auto *DeviceLinkAction =
2785 C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LI, types::TY_Image);
2786 DA.add(*DeviceLinkAction, *ToolChains[0],
2787 CudaArchToString(GpuArchList[I]), AssociatedOffloadKind);
2788 ++I;
2789 }
2790 }
2791 };
2792
2793 /// OpenMP action builder. The host bitcode is passed to the device frontend
2794 /// and all the device linked images are passed to the host link phase.
2795 class OpenMPActionBuilder final : public DeviceActionBuilder {
2796 /// The OpenMP actions for the current input.
2797 ActionList OpenMPDeviceActions;
2798
2799 /// The linker inputs obtained for each toolchain.
2800 SmallVector<ActionList, 8> DeviceLinkerInputs;
2801
2802 public:
2803 OpenMPActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
2804 const Driver::InputList &Inputs)
2805 : DeviceActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs, Action::OFK_OpenMP) {}
2806
2807 ActionBuilderReturnCode
2808 getDeviceDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA,
2809 phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
2810 PhasesTy &Phases) override {
2811 if (OpenMPDeviceActions.empty())
2812 return ABRT_Inactive;
2813
2814 // We should always have an action for each input.
2815 assert(OpenMPDeviceActions.size() == ToolChains.size() &&
2816 "Number of OpenMP actions and toolchains do not match.");
2817
2818 // The host only depends on device action in the linking phase, when all
2819 // the device images have to be embedded in the host image.
2820 if (CurPhase == phases::Link) {
2821 assert(ToolChains.size() == DeviceLinkerInputs.size() &&
2822 "Toolchains and linker inputs sizes do not match.");
2823 auto LI = DeviceLinkerInputs.begin();
2824 for (auto *A : OpenMPDeviceActions) {
2825 LI->push_back(A);
2826 ++LI;
2827 }
2828
2829 // We passed the device action as a host dependence, so we don't need to
2830 // do anything else with them.
2831 OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
2832 return ABRT_Success;
2833 }
2834
2835 // By default, we produce an action for each device arch.
2836 for (Action *&A : OpenMPDeviceActions)
2837 A = C.getDriver().ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, CurPhase, A);
2838
2839 return ABRT_Success;
2840 }
2841
2842 ActionBuilderReturnCode addDeviceDepences(Action *HostAction) override {
2843
2844 // If this is an input action replicate it for each OpenMP toolchain.
2845 if (auto *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(HostAction)) {
2846 OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
2847 for (unsigned I = 0; I < ToolChains.size(); ++I)
2848 OpenMPDeviceActions.push_back(
2849 C.MakeAction<InputAction>(IA->getInputArg(), IA->getType()));
2850 return ABRT_Success;
2851 }
2852
2853 // If this is an unbundling action use it as is for each OpenMP toolchain.
2854 if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction)) {
2855 OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
2856 auto *IA = cast<InputAction>(UA->getInputs().back());
2857 std::string FileName = IA->getInputArg().getAsString(Args);
2858 // Check if the type of the file is the same as the action. Do not
2859 // unbundle it if it is not. Do not unbundle .so files, for example,
2860 // which are not object files.
2861 if (IA->getType() == types::TY_Object &&
2862 (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(FileName) ||
2863 types::lookupTypeForExtension(
2864 llvm::sys::path::extension(FileName).drop_front()) !=
2865 types::TY_Object))
2866 return ABRT_Inactive;
2867 for (unsigned I = 0; I < ToolChains.size(); ++I) {
2868 OpenMPDeviceActions.push_back(UA);
2869 UA->registerDependentActionInfo(
2870 ToolChains[I], /*BoundArch=*/StringRef(), Action::OFK_OpenMP);
2871 }
2872 return ABRT_Success;
2873 }
2874
2875 // When generating code for OpenMP we use the host compile phase result as
2876 // a dependence to the device compile phase so that it can learn what
2877 // declarations should be emitted. However, this is not the only use for
2878 // the host action, so we prevent it from being collapsed.
2879 if (isa<CompileJobAction>(HostAction)) {
2880 HostAction->setCannotBeCollapsedWithNextDependentAction();
2881 assert(ToolChains.size() == OpenMPDeviceActions.size() &&
2882 "Toolchains and device action sizes do not match.");
2883 OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
2884 *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
2885 /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
2886 auto TC = ToolChains.begin();
2887 for (Action *&A : OpenMPDeviceActions) {
2888 assert(isa<CompileJobAction>(A));
2889 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDep;
2890 DDep.add(*A, **TC, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
2891 A = C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDep);
2892 ++TC;
2893 }
2894 }
2895 return ABRT_Success;
2896 }
2897
2898 void appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL) override {
2899 if (OpenMPDeviceActions.empty())
2900 return;
2901
2902 // We should always have an action for each input.
2903 assert(OpenMPDeviceActions.size() == ToolChains.size() &&
2904 "Number of OpenMP actions and toolchains do not match.");
2905
2906 // Append all device actions followed by the proper offload action.
2907 auto TI = ToolChains.begin();
2908 for (auto *A : OpenMPDeviceActions) {
2909 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences Dep;
2910 Dep.add(*A, **TI, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, Action::OFK_OpenMP);
2911 AL.push_back(C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(Dep, A->getType()));
2912 ++TI;
2913 }
2914 // We no longer need the action stored in this builder.
2915 OpenMPDeviceActions.clear();
2916 }
2917
2918 void appendLinkDependences(OffloadAction::DeviceDependences &DA) override {
2919 assert(ToolChains.size() == DeviceLinkerInputs.size() &&
2920 "Toolchains and linker inputs sizes do not match.");
2921
2922 // Append a new link action for each device.
2923 auto TC = ToolChains.begin();
2924 for (auto &LI : DeviceLinkerInputs) {
2925 auto *DeviceLinkAction =
2926 C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LI, types::TY_Image);
2927 DA.add(*DeviceLinkAction, **TC, /*BoundArch=*/nullptr,
2928 Action::OFK_OpenMP);
2929 ++TC;
2930 }
2931 }
2932
2933 bool initialize() override {
2934 // Get the OpenMP toolchains. If we don't get any, the action builder will
2935 // know there is nothing to do related to OpenMP offloading.
2936 auto OpenMPTCRange = C.getOffloadToolChains<Action::OFK_OpenMP>();
2937 for (auto TI = OpenMPTCRange.first, TE = OpenMPTCRange.second; TI != TE;
2938 ++TI)
2939 ToolChains.push_back(TI->second);
2940
2941 DeviceLinkerInputs.resize(ToolChains.size());
2942 return false;
2943 }
2944
2945 bool canUseBundlerUnbundler() const override {
2946 // OpenMP should use bundled files whenever possible.
2947 return true;
2948 }
2949 };

2951 ///
2952 /// TODO: Add the implementation for other specialized builders here.
2953 ///
2954
2955 /// Specialized builders being used by this offloading action builder.
2956 SmallVector<DeviceActionBuilder *, 4> SpecializedBuilders;
2957
2958 /// Flag set to true if all valid builders allow file bundling/unbundling.
2959 bool CanUseBundler;
2960
2961public:
2962 OffloadingActionBuilder(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
2963 const Driver::InputList &Inputs)
2964 : C(C) {
2965 // Create a specialized builder for each device toolchain.
2966
2967 IsValid = true;
2968
2969 // Create a specialized builder for CUDA.
2970 SpecializedBuilders.push_back(new CudaActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs));
2971
2972 // Create a specialized builder for HIP.
2973 SpecializedBuilders.push_back(new HIPActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs));
2974
2975 // Create a specialized builder for OpenMP.
2976 SpecializedBuilders.push_back(new OpenMPActionBuilder(C, Args, Inputs));
2977
2978 //
2979 // TODO: Build other specialized builders here.
2980 //
2981
2982 // Initialize all the builders, keeping track of errors. If all valid
2983 // builders agree that we can use bundling, set the flag to true.
2984 unsigned ValidBuilders = 0u;
2985 unsigned ValidBuildersSupportingBundling = 0u;
2986 for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
2987 IsValid = IsValid && !SB->initialize();
2988
2989 // Update the counters if the builder is valid.
2990 if (SB->isValid()) {
2991 ++ValidBuilders;
2992 if (SB->canUseBundlerUnbundler())
2993 ++ValidBuildersSupportingBundling;
2994 }
2995 }
2996 CanUseBundler =
2997 ValidBuilders && ValidBuilders == ValidBuildersSupportingBundling;
2998 }
2999
3000 ~OffloadingActionBuilder() {
3001 for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders)
3002 delete SB;
3003 }
3004
3005 /// Generate an action that adds device dependences (if any) to a host action.
3006 /// If no device dependence actions exist, just return the host action \a
3007 /// HostAction. If an error is found or if no builder requires the host action
3008 /// to be generated, return nullptr.
3009 Action *
3010 addDeviceDependencesToHostAction(Action *HostAction, const Arg *InputArg,
3011 phases::ID CurPhase, phases::ID FinalPhase,
3012 DeviceActionBuilder::PhasesTy &Phases) {
3013 if (!IsValid)
3014 return nullptr;
3015
3016 if (SpecializedBuilders.empty())
3017 return HostAction;
3018
3019 assert(HostAction && "Invalid host action!");
3020
3021 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDeps;
3022 // Check if all the programming models agree we should not emit the host
3023 // action. Also, keep track of the offloading kinds employed.
3024 auto &OffloadKind = InputArgToOffloadKindMap[InputArg];
3025 unsigned InactiveBuilders = 0u;
3026 unsigned IgnoringBuilders = 0u;
3027 for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
3028 if (!SB->isValid()) {
3029 ++InactiveBuilders;
3030 continue;
3031 }
3032
3033 auto RetCode =
3034 SB->getDeviceDependences(DDeps, CurPhase, FinalPhase, Phases);
3035
3036 // If the builder explicitly says the host action should be ignored,
3037 // we need to increment the variable that tracks the builders that request
3038 // the host object to be ignored.
3039 if (RetCode == DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Ignore_Host)
3040 ++IgnoringBuilders;
3041
3042 // Unless the builder was inactive for this action, we have to record the
3043 // offload kind because the host will have to use it.
3044 if (RetCode != DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Inactive)
3045 OffloadKind |= SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind();
3046 }
3047
3048 // If all builders agree that the host object should be ignored, just return
3049 // nullptr.
3050 if (IgnoringBuilders &&
3051 SpecializedBuilders.size() == (InactiveBuilders + IgnoringBuilders))
3052 return nullptr;
3053
3054 if (DDeps.getActions().empty())
3055 return HostAction;
3056
3057 // We have dependences we need to bundle together. We use an offload action
3058 // for that.
3059 OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
3060 *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
3061 /*BoundArch=*/nullptr, DDeps);
3062 return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDeps);
3063 }
3064
3065 /// Generate an action that adds a host dependence to a device action. The
3066 /// results will be kept in this action builder. Return true if an error was
3067 /// found.
3068 bool addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Action *&HostAction,
3069 const Arg *InputArg) {
3070 if (!IsValid)
3071 return true;
3072
3073 // If we are supporting bundling/unbundling and the current action is an
3074 // input action of non-source file, we replace the host action by the
3075 // unbundling action. The bundler tool has the logic to detect if an input
3076 // is a bundle or not and if the input is not a bundle it assumes it is a
3077 // host file. Therefore it is safe to create an unbundling action even if
3078 // the input is not a bundle.
3079 if (CanUseBundler && isa<InputAction>(HostAction) &&
3080 InputArg->getOption().getKind() == llvm::opt::Option::InputClass &&
3081 !types::isSrcFile(HostAction->getType())) {
3082 auto UnbundlingHostAction =
3083 C.MakeAction<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction);
3084 UnbundlingHostAction->registerDependentActionInfo(
3085 C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
3086 /*BoundArch=*/StringRef(), Action::OFK_Host);
3087 HostAction = UnbundlingHostAction;
3088 }
3089
3090 assert(HostAction && "Invalid host action!");
3091
3092 // Register the offload kinds that are used.
3093 auto &OffloadKind = InputArgToOffloadKindMap[InputArg];
3094 for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
3095 if (!SB->isValid())
3096 continue;
3097
3098 auto RetCode = SB->addDeviceDepences(HostAction);
3099
3100 // Host dependences for device actions are not compatible with that same
3101 // action being ignored.
3102 assert(RetCode != DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Ignore_Host &&
3103 "Host dependence not expected to be ignored.!");
3104
3105 // Unless the builder was inactive for this action, we have to record the
3106 // offload kind because the host will have to use it.
3107 if (RetCode != DeviceActionBuilder::ABRT_Inactive)
3108 OffloadKind |= SB->getAssociatedOffloadKind();
3109 }
3110
3111 // Do not use unbundler if the Host does not depend on device action.
3112 if (OffloadKind == Action::OFK_None && CanUseBundler)
3113 if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(HostAction))
3114 HostAction = UA->getInputs().back();
3115
3116 return false;
3117 }
3118
3119 /// Add the offloading top level actions to the provided action list. This
3120 /// function can replace the host action by a bundling action if the
3121 /// programming models allow it.
3122 bool appendTopLevelActions(ActionList &AL, Action *HostAction,
3123 const Arg *InputArg) {
3124 // Get the device actions to be appended.
3125 ActionList OffloadAL;
3126 for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
3127 if (!SB->isValid())
3128 continue;
3129 SB->appendTopLevelActions(OffloadAL);
3130 }
3131
3132 // If we can use the bundler, replace the host action by the bundling one in
3133 // the resulting list. Otherwise, just append the device actions. For
3134 // device only compilation, HostAction is a null pointer, therefore only do
3135 // this when HostAction is not a null pointer.
3136 if (CanUseBundler && HostAction && !OffloadAL.empty()) {
3137 // Add the host action to the list in order to create the bundling action.
3138 OffloadAL.push_back(HostAction);
3139
3140 // We expect that the host action was just appended to the action list
3141 // before this method was called.
3142 assert(HostAction == AL.back() && "Host action not in the list??");
3143 HostAction = C.MakeAction<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(OffloadAL);
3144 AL.back() = HostAction;
3145 } else
3146 AL.append(OffloadAL.begin(), OffloadAL.end());
3147
3148 // Propagate to the current host action (if any) the offload information
3149 // associated with the current input.
3150 if (HostAction)
3151 HostAction->propagateHostOffloadInfo(InputArgToOffloadKindMap[InputArg],
3152 /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
3153 return false;
3154 }
3155
3156 /// Processes the host linker action. This currently consists of replacing it
3157 /// with an offload action if there are device link objects and propagate to
3158 /// the host action all the offload kinds used in the current compilation. The
3159 /// resulting action is returned.
3160 Action *processHostLinkAction(Action *HostAction) {
3161 // Add all the dependences from the device linking actions.
3162 OffloadAction::DeviceDependences DDeps;
3163 for (auto *SB : SpecializedBuilders) {
3164 if (!SB->isValid())
3165 continue;
3166
3167 SB->appendLinkDependences(DDeps);
3168 }
3169
3170 // Calculate all the offload kinds used in the current compilation.
3171 unsigned ActiveOffloadKinds = 0u;
3172 for (auto &I : InputArgToOffloadKindMap)
3173 ActiveOffloadKinds |= I.second;
3174
3175 // If we don't have device dependencies, we don't have to create an offload
3176 // action.
3177 if (DDeps.getActions().empty()) {
3178 // Propagate all the active kinds to host action. Given that it is a link
3179 // action it is assumed to depend on all actions generated so far.
3180 HostAction->propagateHostOffloadInfo(ActiveOffloadKinds,
3181 /*BoundArch=*/nullptr);
3182 return HostAction;
3183 }
3184
3185 // Create the offload action with all dependences. When an offload action
3186 // is created the kinds are propagated to the host action, so we don't have
3187 // to do that explicitly here.
3188 OffloadAction::HostDependence HDep(
3189 *HostAction, *C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>(),
3190 /*BoundArch*/ nullptr, ActiveOffloadKinds);
3191 return C.MakeAction<OffloadAction>(HDep, DDeps);
3192 }
3193};
3194} // anonymous namespace.
3195
3196void Driver::BuildActions(Compilation &C, DerivedArgList &Args,
3197 const InputList &Inputs, ActionList &Actions) const {
3198 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building compilation actions");
3199
3200 if (!SuppressMissingInputWarning && Inputs.empty()) {
3201 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_no_input_files);
3202 return;
3203 }
3204
3205 Arg *FinalPhaseArg;
3206 phases::ID FinalPhase = getFinalPhase(Args, &FinalPhaseArg);
3207
3208 if (FinalPhase == phases::Link) {
3209 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm))
3210 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_emit_llvm_link);
3211 if (IsCLMode() && LTOMode != LTOK_None &&
3212 !Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fuse_ld_EQ).equals_lower("lld"))
3213 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_lto_without_lld);
3214 }
3215
3216 // Reject -Z* at the top level, these options should never have been exposed
3217 // by gcc.
3218 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_Z_Joined))
3219 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_use_of_Z_option) << A->getAsString(Args);
3220
3221 // Diagnose misuse of /Fo.
3222 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo)) {
3223 StringRef V = A->getValue();
3224 if (Inputs.size() > 1 && !V.empty() &&
3225 !llvm::sys::path::is_separator(V.back())) {
3226 // Check whether /Fo tries to name an output file for multiple inputs.
3227 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_out_file_argument_with_multiple_sources)
3228 << A->getSpelling() << V;
3229 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo);
3230 }
3231 }
3232
3233 // Diagnose misuse of /Fa.
3234 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa)) {
3235 StringRef V = A->getValue();
3236 if (Inputs.size() > 1 && !V.empty() &&
3237 !llvm::sys::path::is_separator(V.back())) {
3238 // Check whether /Fa tries to name an asm file for multiple inputs.
3239 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_out_file_argument_with_multiple_sources)
3240 << A->getSpelling() << V;
3241 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa);
3242 }
3243 }
3244
3245 // Diagnose misuse of /o.
3246 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
3247 if (A->getValue()[0] == '\0') {
3248 // It has to have a value.
3249 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_missing_argument) << A->getSpelling() << 1;
3250 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_o);
3251 }
3252 }
3253
3254 // Ignore /Yc/Yu if both /Yc and /Yu passed but with different filenames.
3255 Arg *YcArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
3256 Arg *YuArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
3257 if (YcArg && YuArg && strcmp(YcArg->getValue(), YuArg->getValue()) != 0) {
3258 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_ycyu_different_arg_clang_cl);
3259 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
3260 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
3261 YcArg = YuArg = nullptr;
3262 }
3263 if (YcArg && Inputs.size() > 1) {
3264 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_yc_multiple_inputs_clang_cl);
3265 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
3266 YcArg = nullptr;
3267 }
3268 if (FinalPhase == phases::Preprocess || Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Y_)) {
3269 // If only preprocessing or /Y- is used, all pch handling is disabled.
3270 // Rather than check for it everywhere, just remove clang-cl pch-related
3271 // flags here.
3272 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fp);
3273 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
3274 Args.eraseArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
3275 YcArg = YuArg = nullptr;
3276 }
3277
3278 // Builder to be used to build offloading actions.
3279 OffloadingActionBuilder OffloadBuilder(C, Args, Inputs);
3280
3281 // Construct the actions to perform.
3282 HeaderModulePrecompileJobAction *HeaderModuleAction = nullptr;
3283 ActionList LinkerInputs;
3284
3285 llvm::SmallVector<phases::ID, phases::MaxNumberOfPhases> PL;
3286 for (auto &I : Inputs) {
3287 types::ID InputType = I.first;
3288 const Arg *InputArg = I.second;
3289
3290 PL.clear();
3291 types::getCompilationPhases(InputType, PL);
3292
3293 // If the first step comes after the final phase we are doing as part of
3294 // this compilation, warn the user about it.
3295 phases::ID InitialPhase = PL[0];
3296 if (InitialPhase > FinalPhase) {
3297 if (InputArg->isClaimed())
3298 continue;
3299
3300 // Claim here to avoid the more general unused warning.
3301 InputArg->claim();
3302
3303 // Suppress all unused style warnings with -Qunused-arguments
3304 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_Qunused_arguments))
3305 continue;
3306
3307 // Special case when final phase determined by binary name, rather than
3308 // by a command-line argument with a corresponding Arg.
3309 if (CCCIsCPP())
3310 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_input_file_unused_by_cpp)
3311 << InputArg->getAsString(Args) << getPhaseName(InitialPhase);
3312 // Special case '-E' warning on a previously preprocessed file to make
3313 // more sense.
3314 else if (InitialPhase == phases::Compile &&
3315 FinalPhase == phases::Preprocess &&
3316 getPreprocessedType(InputType) == types::TY_INVALID)
3317 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_preprocessed_input_file_unused)
3318 << InputArg->getAsString(Args) << !!FinalPhaseArg
3319 << (FinalPhaseArg ? FinalPhaseArg->getOption().getName() : "");
3320 else
3321 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_input_file_unused)
3322 << InputArg->getAsString(Args) << getPhaseName(InitialPhase)
3323 << !!FinalPhaseArg
3324 << (FinalPhaseArg ? FinalPhaseArg->getOption().getName() : "");
3325 continue;
3326 }
3327
3328 if (YcArg) {
3329 // Add a separate precompile phase for the compile phase.
3330 if (FinalPhase >= phases::Compile) {
3331 const types::ID HeaderType = lookupHeaderTypeForSourceType(InputType);
3332 llvm::SmallVector<phases::ID, phases::MaxNumberOfPhases> PCHPL;
3333 types::getCompilationPhases(HeaderType, PCHPL);
3334 // Build the pipeline for the pch file.
3335 Action *ClangClPch =
3336 C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, HeaderType);
3337 for (phases::ID Phase : PCHPL)
3338 ClangClPch = ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, Phase, ClangClPch);
3339 assert(ClangClPch);
3340 Actions.push_back(ClangClPch);
3341 // The driver currently exits after the first failed command. This
3342 // relies on that behavior, to make sure if the pch generation fails,
3343 // the main compilation won't run.
3344 // FIXME: If the main compilation fails, the PCH generation should
3345 // probably not be considered successful either.
3346 }
3347 }
3348
3349 // Build the pipeline for this file.
3350 Action *Current = C.MakeAction<InputAction>(*InputArg, InputType);
3351
3352 // Use the current host action in any of the offloading actions, if
3353 // required.
3354 if (OffloadBuilder.addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Current, InputArg))
3355 break;
3356
3357 for (SmallVectorImpl<phases::ID>::iterator i = PL.begin(), e = PL.end();
3358 i != e; ++i) {
3359 phases::ID Phase = *i;
3360
3361 // We are done if this step is past what the user requested.
3362 if (Phase > FinalPhase)
3363 break;
3364
3365 // Add any offload action the host action depends on.
3366 Current = OffloadBuilder.addDeviceDependencesToHostAction(
3367 Current, InputArg, Phase, FinalPhase, PL);
3368 if (!Current)
3369 break;
3370
3371 // Queue linker inputs.
3372 if (Phase == phases::Link) {
3373 assert((i + 1) == e && "linking must be final compilation step.");
3374 LinkerInputs.push_back(Current);
3375 Current = nullptr;
3376 break;
3377 }
3378
3379 // Each precompiled header file after a module file action is a module
3380 // header of that same module file, rather than being compiled to a
3381 // separate PCH.
3382 if (Phase == phases::Precompile && HeaderModuleAction &&
3383 getPrecompiledType(InputType) == types::TY_PCH) {
3384 HeaderModuleAction->addModuleHeaderInput(Current);
3385 Current = nullptr;
3386 break;
3387 }
3388
3389 // FIXME: Should we include any prior module file outputs as inputs of
3390 // later actions in the same command line?
3391
3392 // Otherwise construct the appropriate action.
3393 Action *NewCurrent = ConstructPhaseAction(C, Args, Phase, Current);
3394
3395 // We didn't create a new action, so we will just move to the next phase.
3396 if (NewCurrent == Current)
3397 continue;
3398
3399 if (auto *HMA = dyn_cast<HeaderModulePrecompileJobAction>(NewCurrent))
3400 HeaderModuleAction = HMA;
3401
3402 Current = NewCurrent;
3403
3404 // Use the current host action in any of the offloading actions, if
3405 // required.
3406 if (OffloadBuilder.addHostDependenceToDeviceActions(Current, InputArg))
3407 break;
3408
3409 if (Current->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
3410 break;
3411 }
3412
3413 // If we ended with something, add to the output list.
3414 if (Current)
3415 Actions.push_back(Current);
3416
3417 // Add any top level actions generated for offloading.
3418 OffloadBuilder.appendTopLevelActions(Actions, Current, InputArg);
3419 }
3420
3421 // Add a link action if necessary.
3422 if (!LinkerInputs.empty()) {
3423 Action *LA = C.MakeAction<LinkJobAction>(LinkerInputs, types::TY_Image);
3424 LA = OffloadBuilder.processHostLinkAction(LA);
3425 Actions.push_back(LA);
3426 }
3427
3428 // If we are linking, claim any options which are obviously only used for
3429 // compilation.
3430 if (FinalPhase == phases::Link && PL.size() == 1) {
3431 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_CompileOnly_Group);
3432 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cl_compile_Group);
3433 }
3434
3435 // Claim ignored clang-cl options.
3436 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cl_ignored_Group);
3437
3438 // Claim --cuda-host-only and --cuda-compile-host-device, which may be passed
3439 // to non-CUDA compilations and should not trigger warnings there.
3440 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cuda_host_only);
3441 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cuda_compile_host_device);
3442}
3443
3444Action *Driver::ConstructPhaseAction(
3445 Compilation &C, const ArgList &Args, phases::ID Phase, Action *Input,
3446 Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
3447 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Constructing phase actions");
3448
3449 // Some types skip the assembler phase (e.g., llvm-bc), but we can't
3450 // encode this in the steps because the intermediate type depends on
3451 // arguments. Just special case here.
3452 if (Phase == phases::Assemble && Input->getType() != types::TY_PP_Asm)
3453 return Input;
3454
3455 // Build the appropriate action.
3456 switch (Phase) {
3457 case phases::Link:
3458 llvm_unreachable("link action invalid here.");
3459 case phases::Preprocess: {
3460 types::ID OutputTy;
3461 // -{M, MM} alter the output type.
3462 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM)) {
3463 OutputTy = types::TY_Dependencies;
3464 } else {
3465 OutputTy = Input->getType();
3466 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frewrite_includes,
3467 options::OPT_fno_rewrite_includes, false) &&
3468 !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_frewrite_imports,
3469 options::OPT_fno_rewrite_imports, false) &&
3470 !CCGenDiagnostics)
3471 OutputTy = types::getPreprocessedType(OutputTy);
3472 assert(OutputTy != types::TY_INVALID &&
3473 "Cannot preprocess this input type!");
3474 }
3475 return C.MakeAction<PreprocessJobAction>(Input, OutputTy);
3476 }
3477 case phases::Precompile: {
3478 types::ID OutputTy = getPrecompiledType(Input->getType());
3479 assert(OutputTy != types::TY_INVALID &&
3480 "Cannot precompile this input type!");
3481
3482 // If we're given a module name, precompile header file inputs as a
3483 // module, not as a precompiled header.
3484 const char *ModName = nullptr;
3485 if (OutputTy == types::TY_PCH) {
3486 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodule_name_EQ))
3487 ModName = A->getValue();
3488 if (ModName)
3489 OutputTy = types::TY_ModuleFile;
3490 }
3491
3492 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only)) {
3493 // Syntax checks should not emit a PCH file
3494 OutputTy = types::TY_Nothing;
3495 }
3496
3497 if (ModName)
3498 return C.MakeAction<HeaderModulePrecompileJobAction>(Input, OutputTy,
3499 ModName);
3500 return C.MakeAction<PrecompileJobAction>(Input, OutputTy);
3501 }
3502 case phases::Compile: {
3503 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fsyntax_only))
3504 return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Nothing);
3505 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc))
3506 return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_RewrittenObjC);
3507 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_legacy_objc))
3508 return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input,
3509 types::TY_RewrittenLegacyObjC);
3510 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__analyze, options::OPT__analyze_auto))
3511 return C.MakeAction<AnalyzeJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Plist);
3512 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__migrate))
3513 return C.MakeAction<MigrateJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Remap);
3514 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_ast))
3515 return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_AST);
3516 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_module_file_info))
3517 return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_ModuleFile);
3518 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_verify_pch))
3519 return C.MakeAction<VerifyPCHJobAction>(Input, types::TY_Nothing);
3520 return C.MakeAction<CompileJobAction>(Input, types::TY_LLVM_BC);
3521 }
3522 case phases::Backend: {
3523 if (isUsingLTO() && TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_None) {
3524 types::ID Output =
3525 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S) ? types::TY_LTO_IR : types::TY_LTO_BC;
3526 return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, Output);
3527 }
3528 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm)) {
3529 types::ID Output =
3530 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_S) ? types::TY_LLVM_IR : types::TY_LLVM_BC;
3531 return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, Output);
3532 }
3533 return C.MakeAction<BackendJobAction>(Input, types::TY_PP_Asm);
3534 }
3535 case phases::Assemble:
3536 return C.MakeAction<AssembleJobAction>(std::move(Input), types::TY_Object);
3537 }
3538
3539 llvm_unreachable("invalid phase in ConstructPhaseAction");
3540}
3541
3542void Driver::BuildJobs(Compilation &C) const {
3543 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building compilation jobs");
3544
3545 Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o);
3546
3547 // It is an error to provide a -o option if we are making multiple output
3548 // files.
3549 if (FinalOutput) {
3550 unsigned NumOutputs = 0;
3551 for (const Action *A : C.getActions())
3552 if (A->getType() != types::TY_Nothing)
3553 ++NumOutputs;
3554
3555 if (NumOutputs > 1) {
3556 Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_output_argument_with_multiple_files);
3557 FinalOutput = nullptr;
3558 }
3559 }
3560
3561 // Collect the list of architectures.
3562 llvm::StringSet<> ArchNames;
3563 if (C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO())
3564 for (const Arg *A : C.getArgs())
3565 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_arch))
3566 ArchNames.insert(A->getValue());
3567
3568 // Set of (Action, canonical ToolChain triple) pairs we've built jobs for.
3569 std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfo> CachedResults;
3570 for (Action *A : C.getActions()) {
3571 // If we are linking an image for multiple archs then the linker wants
3572 // -arch_multiple and -final_output <final image name>. Unfortunately, this
3573 // doesn't fit in cleanly because we have to pass this information down.
3574 //
3575 // FIXME: This is a hack; find a cleaner way to integrate this into the
3576 // process.
3577 const char *LinkingOutput = nullptr;
3578 if (isa<LipoJobAction>(A)) {
3579 if (FinalOutput)
3580 LinkingOutput = FinalOutput->getValue();
3581 else
3582 LinkingOutput = getDefaultImageName();
3583 }
3584
3585 BuildJobsForAction(C, A, &C.getDefaultToolChain(),
3586 /*BoundArch*/ StringRef(),
3587 /*AtTopLevel*/ true,
3588 /*MultipleArchs*/ ArchNames.size() > 1,
3589 /*LinkingOutput*/ LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
3590 /*TargetDeviceOffloadKind*/ Action::OFK_None);
3591 }
3592
3593 // If the user passed -Qunused-arguments or there were errors, don't warn
3594 // about any unused arguments.
3595 if (Diags.hasErrorOccurred() ||
3596 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_Qunused_arguments))
3597 return;
3598
3599 // Claim -### here.
3600 (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH);
3601
3602 // Claim --driver-mode, --rsp-quoting, it was handled earlier.
3603 (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_driver_mode);
3604 (void)C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_rsp_quoting);
3605
3606 for (Arg *A : C.getArgs()) {
3607 // FIXME: It would be nice to be able to send the argument to the
3608 // DiagnosticsEngine, so that extra values, position, and so on could be
3609 // printed.
3610 if (!A->isClaimed()) {
3611 if (A->getOption().hasFlag(options::NoArgumentUnused))
3612 continue;
3613
3614 // Suppress the warning automatically if this is just a flag, and it is an
3615 // instance of an argument we already claimed.
3616 const Option &Opt = A->getOption();
3617 if (Opt.getKind() == Option::FlagClass) {
3618 bool DuplicateClaimed = false;
3619
3620 for (const Arg *AA : C.getArgs().filtered(&Opt)) {
3621 if (AA->isClaimed()) {
3622 DuplicateClaimed = true;
3623 break;
3624 }
3625 }
3626
3627 if (DuplicateClaimed)
3628 continue;
3629 }
3630
3631 // In clang-cl, don't mention unknown arguments here since they have
3632 // already been warned about.
3633 if (!IsCLMode() || !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_UNKNOWN))
3634 Diag(clang::diag::warn_drv_unused_argument)
3635 << A->getAsString(C.getArgs());
3636 }
3637 }
3638}

3640namespace {
3641/// Utility class to control the collapse of dependent actions and select the
3642/// tools accordingly.
3643class ToolSelector final {
3644 /// The tool chain this selector refers to.
3645 const ToolChain &TC;
3646
3647 /// The compilation this selector refers to.
3648 const Compilation &C;
3649
3650 /// The base action this selector refers to.
3651 const JobAction *BaseAction;
3652
3653 /// Set to true if the current toolchain refers to host actions.
3654 bool IsHostSelector;
3655
3656 /// Set to true if save-temps and embed-bitcode functionalities are active.
3657 bool SaveTemps;
3658 bool EmbedBitcode;
3659
3660 /// Get previous dependent action or null if that does not exist. If
3661 /// \a CanBeCollapsed is false, that action must be legal to collapse or
3662 /// null will be returned.
3663 const JobAction *getPrevDependentAction(const ActionList &Inputs,
3664 ActionList &SavedOffloadAction,
3665 bool CanBeCollapsed = true) {
3666 // An option can be collapsed only if it has a single input.
3667 if (Inputs.size() != 1)
3668 return nullptr;
3669
3670 Action *CurAction = *Inputs.begin();
3671 if (CanBeCollapsed &&
3672 !CurAction->isCollapsingWithNextDependentActionLegal())
3673 return nullptr;
3674
3675 // If the input action is an offload action. Look through it and save any
3676 // offload action that can be dropped in the event of a collapse.
3677 if (auto *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(CurAction)) {
3678 // If the dependent action is a device action, we will attempt to collapse
3679 // only with other device actions. Otherwise, we would do the same but
3680 // with host actions only.
3681 if (!IsHostSelector) {
3682 if (OA->hasSingleDeviceDependence(/*DoNotConsiderHostActions=*/true)) {
3683 CurAction =
3684 OA->getSingleDeviceDependence(/*DoNotConsiderHostActions=*/true);
3685 if (CanBeCollapsed &&
3686 !CurAction->isCollapsingWithNextDependentActionLegal())
3687 return nullptr;
3688 SavedOffloadAction.push_back(OA);
3689 return dyn_cast<JobAction>(CurAction);
3690 }
3691 } else if (OA->hasHostDependence()) {
3692 CurAction = OA->getHostDependence();
3693 if (CanBeCollapsed &&
3694 !CurAction->isCollapsingWithNextDependentActionLegal())
3695 return nullptr;
3696 SavedOffloadAction.push_back(OA);
3697 return dyn_cast<JobAction>(CurAction);
3698 }
3699 return nullptr;
3700 }
3701
3702 return dyn_cast<JobAction>(CurAction);
3703 }
3704
3705 /// Return true if an assemble action can be collapsed.
3706 bool canCollapseAssembleAction() const {
3707 return TC.useIntegratedAs() && !SaveTemps &&
3708 !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_via_file_asm) &&
3709 !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_FA) &&
3710 !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa);
3711 }
3712
3713 /// Return true if a preprocessor action can be collapsed.
3714 bool canCollapsePreprocessorAction() const {
3715 return !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_no_integrated_cpp) &&
3716 !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_traditional_cpp) && !SaveTemps &&
3717 !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc);
3718 }
3719
3720 /// Struct that relates an action with the offload actions that would be
3721 /// collapsed with it.
3722 struct JobActionInfo final {
3723 /// The action this info refers to.
3724 const JobAction *JA = nullptr;
3725 /// The offload actions we need to take care off if this action is
3726 /// collapsed.
3727 ActionList SavedOffloadAction;
3728 };
3729
3730 /// Append collapsed offload actions from the give nnumber of elements in the
3731 /// action info array.
3732 static void AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction,
3733 ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> &ActionInfo,
3734 unsigned ElementNum) {
3735 assert(ElementNum <= ActionInfo.size() && "Invalid number of elements.");
3736 for (unsigned I = 0; I < ElementNum; ++I)
3737 CollapsedOffloadAction.append(ActionInfo[I].SavedOffloadAction.begin(),
3738 ActionInfo[I].SavedOffloadAction.end());
3739 }
3740
3741 /// Functions that attempt to perform the combining. They detect if that is
3742 /// legal, and if so they update the inputs \a Inputs and the offload action
3743 /// that were collapsed in \a CollapsedOffloadAction. A tool that deals with
3744 /// the combined action is returned. If the combining is not legal or if the
3745 /// tool does not exist, null is returned.
3746 /// Currently three kinds of collapsing are supported:
3747 /// - Assemble + Backend + Compile;
3748 /// - Assemble + Backend ;
3749 /// - Backend + Compile.
3750 const Tool *
3751 combineAssembleBackendCompile(ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> ActionInfo,
3752 ActionList &Inputs,
3753 ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
3754 if (ActionInfo.size() < 3 || !canCollapseAssembleAction())
3755 return nullptr;
3756 auto *AJ = dyn_cast<AssembleJobAction>(ActionInfo[0].JA);
3757 auto *BJ = dyn_cast<BackendJobAction>(ActionInfo[1].JA);
3758 auto *CJ = dyn_cast<CompileJobAction>(ActionInfo[2].JA);
3759 if (!AJ || !BJ || !CJ)
3760 return nullptr;
3761
3762 // Get compiler tool.
3763 const Tool *T = TC.SelectTool(*CJ);
3764 if (!T)
3765 return nullptr;
3766
3767 // When using -fembed-bitcode, it is required to have the same tool (clang)
3768 // for both CompilerJA and BackendJA. Otherwise, combine two stages.
3769 if (EmbedBitcode) {
3770 const Tool *BT = TC.SelectTool(*BJ);
3771 if (BT == T)
3772 return nullptr;
3773 }
3774
3775 if (!T->hasIntegratedAssembler())
3776 return nullptr;
3777
3778 Inputs = CJ->getInputs();
3779 AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(CollapsedOffloadAction, ActionInfo,
3780 /*NumElements=*/3);
3781 return T;
3782 }
3783 const Tool *combineAssembleBackend(ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> ActionInfo,
3784 ActionList &Inputs,
3785 ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
3786 if (ActionInfo.size() < 2 || !canCollapseAssembleAction())
3787 return nullptr;
3788 auto *AJ = dyn_cast<AssembleJobAction>(ActionInfo[0].JA);
3789 auto *BJ = dyn_cast<BackendJobAction>(ActionInfo[1].JA);
3790 if (!AJ || !BJ)
3791 return nullptr;
3792
3793 // Retrieve the compile job, backend action must always be preceded by one.
3794 ActionList CompileJobOffloadActions;
3795 auto *CJ = getPrevDependentAction(BJ->getInputs(), CompileJobOffloadActions,
3796 /*CanBeCollapsed=*/false);
3797 if (!AJ || !BJ || !CJ)
3798 return nullptr;
3799
3800 assert(isa<CompileJobAction>(CJ) &&
3801 "Expecting compile job preceding backend job.");
3802
3803 // Get compiler tool.
3804 const Tool *T = TC.SelectTool(*CJ);
3805 if (!T)
3806 return nullptr;
3807
3808 if (!T->hasIntegratedAssembler())
3809 return nullptr;
3810
3811 Inputs = BJ->getInputs();
3812 AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(CollapsedOffloadAction, ActionInfo,
3813 /*NumElements=*/2);
3814 return T;
3815 }
3816 const Tool *combineBackendCompile(ArrayRef<JobActionInfo> ActionInfo,
3817 ActionList &Inputs,
3818 ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
3819 if (ActionInfo.size() < 2)
3820 return nullptr;
3821 auto *BJ = dyn_cast<BackendJobAction>(ActionInfo[0].JA);
3822 auto *CJ = dyn_cast<CompileJobAction>(ActionInfo[1].JA);
3823 if (!BJ || !CJ)
3824 return nullptr;
3825
3826 // Check if the initial input (to the compile job or its predessor if one
3827 // exists) is LLVM bitcode. In that case, no preprocessor step is required
3828 // and we can still collapse the compile and backend jobs when we have
3829 // -save-temps. I.e. there is no need for a separate compile job just to
3830 // emit unoptimized bitcode.
3831 bool InputIsBitcode = true;
3832 for (size_t i = 1; i < ActionInfo.size(); i++)
3833 if (ActionInfo[i].JA->getType() != types::TY_LLVM_BC &&
3834 ActionInfo[i].JA->getType() != types::TY_LTO_BC) {
3835 InputIsBitcode = false;
3836 break;
3837 }
3838 if (!InputIsBitcode && !canCollapsePreprocessorAction())
3839 return nullptr;
3840
3841 // Get compiler tool.
3842 const Tool *T = TC.SelectTool(*CJ);
3843 if (!T)
3844 return nullptr;
3845
3846 if (T->canEmitIR() && ((SaveTemps && !InputIsBitcode) || EmbedBitcode))
3847 return nullptr;
3848
3849 Inputs = CJ->getInputs();
3850 AppendCollapsedOffloadAction(CollapsedOffloadAction, ActionInfo,
3851 /*NumElements=*/2);
3852 return T;
3853 }
3854
3855 /// Updates the inputs if the obtained tool supports combining with
3856 /// preprocessor action, and the current input is indeed a preprocessor
3857 /// action. If combining results in the collapse of offloading actions, those
3858 /// are appended to \a CollapsedOffloadAction.
3859 void combineWithPreprocessor(const Tool *T, ActionList &Inputs,
3860 ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
3861 if (!T || !canCollapsePreprocessorAction() || !T->hasIntegratedCPP())
3862 return;
3863
3864 // Attempt to get a preprocessor action dependence.
3865 ActionList PreprocessJobOffloadActions;
3866 ActionList NewInputs;
3867 for (Action *A : Inputs) {
3868 auto *PJ = getPrevDependentAction({A}, PreprocessJobOffloadActions);
3869 if (!PJ || !isa<PreprocessJobAction>(PJ)) {
3870 NewInputs.push_back(A);
3871 continue;
3872 }
3873
3874 // This is legal to combine. Append any offload action we found and add the
3875 // current input to preprocessor inputs.
3876 CollapsedOffloadAction.append(PreprocessJobOffloadActions.begin(),
3877 PreprocessJobOffloadActions.end());
3878 NewInputs.append(PJ->input_begin(), PJ->input_end());
3879 }
3880 Inputs = NewInputs;
3881 }
3882
3883public:
3884 ToolSelector(const JobAction *BaseAction, const ToolChain &TC,
3885 const Compilation &C, bool SaveTemps, bool EmbedBitcode)
3886 : TC(TC), C(C), BaseAction(BaseAction), SaveTemps(SaveTemps),
3887 EmbedBitcode(EmbedBitcode) {
3888 assert(BaseAction && "Invalid base action.");
3889 IsHostSelector = BaseAction->getOffloadingDeviceKind() == Action::OFK_None;
3890 }
3891
3892 /// Check if a chain of actions can be combined and return the tool that can
3893 /// handle the combination of actions. The pointer to the current inputs \a
3894 /// Inputs and the list of offload actions \a CollapsedOffloadActions
3895 /// connected to collapsed actions are updated accordingly. The latter enables
3896 /// the caller of the selector to process them afterwards instead of just
3897 /// dropping them. If no suitable tool is found, null will be returned.
3898 const Tool *getTool(ActionList &Inputs,
3899 ActionList &CollapsedOffloadAction) {
3900 //
3901 // Get the largest chain of actions that we could combine.
3902 //
3903
3904 SmallVector<JobActionInfo, 5> ActionChain(1);
3905 ActionChain.back().JA = BaseAction;
3906 while (ActionChain.back().JA) {
3907 const Action *CurAction = ActionChain.back().JA;
3908
3909 // Grow the chain by one element.
3910 ActionChain.resize(ActionChain.size() + 1);
3911 JobActionInfo &AI = ActionChain.back();
3912
3913 // Attempt to fill it with the
3914 AI.JA =
3915 getPrevDependentAction(CurAction->getInputs(), AI.SavedOffloadAction);
3916 }
3917
3918 // Pop the last action info as it could not be filled.
3919 ActionChain.pop_back();
3920
3921 //
3922 // Attempt to combine actions. If all combining attempts failed, just return
3923 // the tool of the provided action. At the end we attempt to combine the
3924 // action with any preprocessor action it may depend on.
3925 //
3926
3927 const Tool *T = combineAssembleBackendCompile(ActionChain, Inputs,
3928 CollapsedOffloadAction);
3929 if (!T)
3930 T = combineAssembleBackend(ActionChain, Inputs, CollapsedOffloadAction);
3931 if (!T)
3932 T = combineBackendCompile(ActionChain, Inputs, CollapsedOffloadAction);
3933 if (!T) {
3934 Inputs = BaseAction->getInputs();
3935 T = TC.SelectTool(*BaseAction);
3936 }
3937
3938 combineWithPreprocessor(T, Inputs, CollapsedOffloadAction);
3939 return T;
3940 }
3941};
3942}
