3944/// Return a string that uniquely identifies the result of a job. The bound arch
3945/// is not necessarily represented in the toolchain's triple -- for example,
3946/// armv7 and armv7s both map to the same triple -- so we need both in our map.
3947/// Also, we need to add the offloading device kind, as the same tool chain can
3948/// be used for host and device for some programming models, e.g. OpenMP.
3949static std::string GetTriplePlusArchString(const ToolChain *TC,
3950 StringRef BoundArch,
3951 Action::OffloadKind OffloadKind) {
3952 std::string TriplePlusArch = TC->getTriple().normalize();
3953 if (!BoundArch.empty()) {
3954 TriplePlusArch += "-";
3955 TriplePlusArch += BoundArch;
3956 }
3957 TriplePlusArch += "-";
3958 TriplePlusArch += Action::GetOffloadKindName(OffloadKind);
3959 return TriplePlusArch;
3960}
3961
3962InputInfo Driver::BuildJobsForAction(
3963 Compilation &C, const Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, StringRef BoundArch,
3964 bool AtTopLevel, bool MultipleArchs, const char *LinkingOutput,
3965 std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfo> &CachedResults,
3966 Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
3967 std::pair<const Action *, std::string> ActionTC = {
3968 A, GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)};
3969 auto CachedResult = CachedResults.find(ActionTC);
3970 if (CachedResult != CachedResults.end()) {
3971 return CachedResult->second;
3972 }
3973 InputInfo Result = BuildJobsForActionNoCache(
3974 C, A, TC, BoundArch, AtTopLevel, MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput,
3975 CachedResults, TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
3976 CachedResults[ActionTC] = Result;
3977 return Result;
3978}
3979
3980InputInfo Driver::BuildJobsForActionNoCache(
3981 Compilation &C, const Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, StringRef BoundArch,
3982 bool AtTopLevel, bool MultipleArchs, const char *LinkingOutput,
3983 std::map<std::pair<const Action *, std::string>, InputInfo> &CachedResults,
3984 Action::OffloadKind TargetDeviceOffloadKind) const {
3985 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Building compilation jobs");
3986
3987 InputInfoList OffloadDependencesInputInfo;
3988 bool BuildingForOffloadDevice = TargetDeviceOffloadKind != Action::OFK_None;
3989 if (const OffloadAction *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(A)) {
3990 // The 'Darwin' toolchain is initialized only when its arguments are
3991 // computed. Get the default arguments for OFK_None to ensure that
3992 // initialization is performed before processing the offload action.
3993 // FIXME: Remove when darwin's toolchain is initialized during construction.
3994 C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, Action::OFK_None);
3995
3996 // The offload action is expected to be used in four different situations.
3997 //
3998 // a) Set a toolchain/architecture/kind for a host action:
3999 // Host Action 1 -> OffloadAction -> Host Action 2
4000 //
4001 // b) Set a toolchain/architecture/kind for a device action;
4002 // Device Action 1 -> OffloadAction -> Device Action 2
4003 //
4004 // c) Specify a device dependence to a host action;
4005 // Device Action 1 _
4006 // \
4007 // Host Action 1 ---> OffloadAction -> Host Action 2
4008 //
4009 // d) Specify a host dependence to a device action.
4010 // Host Action 1 _
4011 // \
4012 // Device Action 1 ---> OffloadAction -> Device Action 2
4013 //
4014 // For a) and b), we just return the job generated for the dependence. For
4015 // c) and d) we override the current action with the host/device dependence
4016 // if the current toolchain is host/device and set the offload dependences
4017 // info with the jobs obtained from the device/host dependence(s).
4018
4019 // If there is a single device option, just generate the job for it.
4020 if (OA->hasSingleDeviceDependence()) {
4021 InputInfo DevA;
4022 OA->doOnEachDeviceDependence([&](Action *DepA, const ToolChain *DepTC,
4023 const char *DepBoundArch) {
4024 DevA =
4025 BuildJobsForAction(C, DepA, DepTC, DepBoundArch, AtTopLevel,
4026 /*MultipleArchs*/ !!DepBoundArch, LinkingOutput,
4027 CachedResults, DepA->getOffloadingDeviceKind());
4028 });
4029 return DevA;
4030 }
4031
4032 // If 'Action 2' is host, we generate jobs for the device dependences and
4033 // override the current action with the host dependence. Otherwise, we
4034 // generate the host dependences and override the action with the device
4035 // dependence. The dependences can't therefore be a top-level action.
4036 OA->doOnEachDependence(
4037 /*IsHostDependence=*/BuildingForOffloadDevice,
4038 [&](Action *DepA, const ToolChain *DepTC, const char *DepBoundArch) {
4039 OffloadDependencesInputInfo.push_back(BuildJobsForAction(
4040 C, DepA, DepTC, DepBoundArch, /*AtTopLevel=*/false,
4041 /*MultipleArchs*/ !!DepBoundArch, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
4042 DepA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
4043 });
4044
4045 A = BuildingForOffloadDevice
4046 ? OA->getSingleDeviceDependence(/*DoNotConsiderHostActions=*/true)
4047 : OA->getHostDependence();
4048 }
4049
4050 if (const InputAction *IA = dyn_cast<InputAction>(A)) {
4051 // FIXME: It would be nice to not claim this here; maybe the old scheme of
4052 // just using Args was better?
4053 const Arg &Input = IA->getInputArg();
4054 Input.claim();
4055 if (Input.getOption().matches(options::OPT_INPUT)) {
4056 const char *Name = Input.getValue();
4057 return InputInfo(A, Name, /* BaseInput = */ Name);
4058 }
4059 return InputInfo(A, &Input, /* BaseInput = */ "");
4060 }
4061
4062 if (const BindArchAction *BAA = dyn_cast<BindArchAction>(A)) {
4063 const ToolChain *TC;
4064 StringRef ArchName = BAA->getArchName();
4065
4066 if (!ArchName.empty())
4067 TC = &getToolChain(C.getArgs(),
4068 computeTargetTriple(*this, TargetTriple,
4069 C.getArgs(), ArchName));
4070 else
4071 TC = &C.getDefaultToolChain();
4072
4073 return BuildJobsForAction(C, *BAA->input_begin(), TC, ArchName, AtTopLevel,
4074 MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
4075 TargetDeviceOffloadKind);
4076 }
4077
4078
4079 ActionList Inputs = A->getInputs();
4080
4081 const JobAction *JA = cast<JobAction>(A);
4082 ActionList CollapsedOffloadActions;
4083
4084 ToolSelector TS(JA, *TC, C, isSaveTempsEnabled(),
4085 embedBitcodeInObject() && !isUsingLTO());
4086 const Tool *T = TS.getTool(Inputs, CollapsedOffloadActions);
4087
4088 if (!T)
4089 return InputInfo();
4090
4091 // If we've collapsed action list that contained OffloadAction we
4092 // need to build jobs for host/device-side inputs it may have held.
4093 for (const auto *OA : CollapsedOffloadActions)
4094 cast<OffloadAction>(OA)->doOnEachDependence(
4095 /*IsHostDependence=*/BuildingForOffloadDevice,
4096 [&](Action *DepA, const ToolChain *DepTC, const char *DepBoundArch) {
4097 OffloadDependencesInputInfo.push_back(BuildJobsForAction(
4098 C, DepA, DepTC, DepBoundArch, /* AtTopLevel */ false,
4099 /*MultipleArchs=*/!!DepBoundArch, LinkingOutput, CachedResults,
4100 DepA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
4101 });
4102
4103 // Only use pipes when there is exactly one input.
4104 InputInfoList InputInfos;
4105 for (const Action *Input : Inputs) {
4106 // Treat dsymutil and verify sub-jobs as being at the top-level too, they
4107 // shouldn't get temporary output names.
4108 // FIXME: Clean this up.
4109 bool SubJobAtTopLevel =
4110 AtTopLevel && (isa<DsymutilJobAction>(A) || isa<VerifyJobAction>(A));
4111 InputInfos.push_back(BuildJobsForAction(
4112 C, Input, TC, BoundArch, SubJobAtTopLevel, MultipleArchs, LinkingOutput,
4113 CachedResults, A->getOffloadingDeviceKind()));
4114 }
4115
4116 // Always use the first input as the base input.
4117 const char *BaseInput = InputInfos[0].getBaseInput();
4118
4119 // ... except dsymutil actions, which use their actual input as the base
4120 // input.
4121 if (JA->getType() == types::TY_dSYM)
4122 BaseInput = InputInfos[0].getFilename();
4123
4124 // ... and in header module compilations, which use the module name.
4125 if (auto *ModuleJA = dyn_cast<HeaderModulePrecompileJobAction>(JA))
4126 BaseInput = ModuleJA->getModuleName();
4127
4128 // Append outputs of offload device jobs to the input list
4129 if (!OffloadDependencesInputInfo.empty())
4130 InputInfos.append(OffloadDependencesInputInfo.begin(),
4131 OffloadDependencesInputInfo.end());
4132
4133 // Set the effective triple of the toolchain for the duration of this job.
4134 llvm::Triple EffectiveTriple;
4135 const ToolChain &ToolTC = T->getToolChain();
4136 const ArgList &Args =
4137 C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, A->getOffloadingDeviceKind());
4138 if (InputInfos.size() != 1) {
4139 EffectiveTriple = llvm::Triple(ToolTC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(Args));
4140 } else {
4141 // Pass along the input type if it can be unambiguously determined.
4142 EffectiveTriple = llvm::Triple(
4143 ToolTC.ComputeEffectiveClangTriple(Args, InputInfos[0].getType()));
4144 }
4145 RegisterEffectiveTriple TripleRAII(ToolTC, EffectiveTriple);
4146
4147 // Determine the place to write output to, if any.
4148 InputInfo Result;
4149 InputInfoList UnbundlingResults;
4150 if (auto *UA = dyn_cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(JA)) {
4151 // If we have an unbundling job, we need to create results for all the
4152 // outputs. We also update the results cache so that other actions using
4153 // this unbundling action can get the right results.
4154 for (auto &UI : UA->getDependentActionsInfo()) {
4155 assert(UI.DependentOffloadKind != Action::OFK_None &&
4156 "Unbundling with no offloading??");
4157
4158 // Unbundling actions are never at the top level. When we generate the
4159 // offloading prefix, we also do that for the host file because the
4160 // unbundling action does not change the type of the output which can
4161 // cause a overwrite.
4162 std::string OffloadingPrefix = Action::GetOffloadingFileNamePrefix(
4163 UI.DependentOffloadKind,
4164 UI.DependentToolChain->getTriple().normalize(),
4165 /*CreatePrefixForHost=*/true);
4166 auto CurI = InputInfo(
4167 UA,
4168 GetNamedOutputPath(C, *UA, BaseInput, UI.DependentBoundArch,
4169 /*AtTopLevel=*/false,
4170 MultipleArchs ||
4171 UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP,
4172 OffloadingPrefix),
4173 BaseInput);
4174 // Save the unbundling result.
4175 UnbundlingResults.push_back(CurI);
4176
4177 // Get the unique string identifier for this dependence and cache the
4178 // result.
4179 StringRef Arch;
4180 if (TargetDeviceOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP) {
4181 if (UI.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_Host)
4182 Arch = StringRef();
4183 else
4184 Arch = UI.DependentBoundArch;
4185 } else
4186 Arch = BoundArch;
4187
4188 CachedResults[{A, GetTriplePlusArchString(UI.DependentToolChain, Arch,
4189 UI.DependentOffloadKind)}] =
4190 CurI;
4191 }
4192
4193 // Now that we have all the results generated, select the one that should be
4194 // returned for the current depending action.
4195 std::pair<const Action *, std::string> ActionTC = {
4196 A, GetTriplePlusArchString(TC, BoundArch, TargetDeviceOffloadKind)};
4197 assert(CachedResults.find(ActionTC) != CachedResults.end() &&
4198 "Result does not exist??");
4199 Result = CachedResults[ActionTC];
4200 } else if (JA->getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
4201 Result = InputInfo(A, BaseInput);
4202 else {
4203 // We only have to generate a prefix for the host if this is not a top-level
4204 // action.
4205 std::string OffloadingPrefix = Action::GetOffloadingFileNamePrefix(
4206 A->getOffloadingDeviceKind(), TC->getTriple().normalize(),
4207 /*CreatePrefixForHost=*/!!A->getOffloadingHostActiveKinds() &&
4208 !AtTopLevel);
4209 Result = InputInfo(A, GetNamedOutputPath(C, *JA, BaseInput, BoundArch,
4210 AtTopLevel, MultipleArchs,
4211 OffloadingPrefix),
4212 BaseInput);
4213 }
4214
4215 if (CCCPrintBindings && !CCGenDiagnostics) {
4216 llvm::errs() << "# \"" << T->getToolChain().getTripleString() << '"'
4217 << " - \"" << T->getName() << "\", inputs: [";
4218 for (unsigned i = 0, e = InputInfos.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4219 llvm::errs() << InputInfos[i].getAsString();
4220 if (i + 1 != e)
4221 llvm::errs() << ", ";
4222 }
4223 if (UnbundlingResults.empty())
4224 llvm::errs() << "], output: " << Result.getAsString() << "\n";
4225 else {
4226 llvm::errs() << "], outputs: [";
4227 for (unsigned i = 0, e = UnbundlingResults.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4228 llvm::errs() << UnbundlingResults[i].getAsString();
4229 if (i + 1 != e)
4230 llvm::errs() << ", ";
4231 }
4232 llvm::errs() << "] \n";
4233 }
4234 } else {
4235 if (UnbundlingResults.empty())
4236 T->ConstructJob(
4237 C, *JA, Result, InputInfos,
4238 C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, JA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()),
4239 LinkingOutput);
4240 else
4241 T->ConstructJobMultipleOutputs(
4242 C, *JA, UnbundlingResults, InputInfos,
4243 C.getArgsForToolChain(TC, BoundArch, JA->getOffloadingDeviceKind()),
4244 LinkingOutput);
4245 }
4246 return Result;
4247}
4248
4249const char *Driver::getDefaultImageName() const {
4250 llvm::Triple Target(llvm::Triple::normalize(TargetTriple));
4251 return Target.isOSWindows() ? "a.exe" : "a.out";
4252}
4253
4254/// Create output filename based on ArgValue, which could either be a
4255/// full filename, filename without extension, or a directory. If ArgValue
4256/// does not provide a filename, then use BaseName, and use the extension
4257/// suitable for FileType.
4258static const char *MakeCLOutputFilename(const ArgList &Args, StringRef ArgValue,
4259 StringRef BaseName,
4260 types::ID FileType) {
4261 SmallString<128> Filename = ArgValue;
4262
4263 if (ArgValue.empty()) {
4264 // If the argument is empty, output to BaseName in the current dir.
4265 Filename = BaseName;
4266 } else if (llvm::sys::path::is_separator(Filename.back())) {
4267 // If the argument is a directory, output to BaseName in that dir.
4268 llvm::sys::path::append(Filename, BaseName);
4269 }
4270
4271 if (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(ArgValue)) {
4272 // If the argument didn't provide an extension, then set it.
4273 const char *Extension = types::getTypeTempSuffix(FileType, true);
4274
4275 if (FileType == types::TY_Image &&
4276 Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LD, options::OPT__SLASH_LDd)) {
4277 // The output file is a dll.
4278 Extension = "dll";
4279 }
4280
4281 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Filename, Extension);
4282 }
4283
4284 return Args.MakeArgString(Filename.c_str());
4285}
4286
4287const char *Driver::GetNamedOutputPath(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
4288 const char *BaseInput,
4289 StringRef BoundArch, bool AtTopLevel,
4290 bool MultipleArchs,
4291 StringRef OffloadingPrefix) const {
4292 llvm::PrettyStackTraceString CrashInfo("Computing output path");
4293 // Output to a user requested destination?
4294 if (AtTopLevel && !isa<DsymutilJobAction>(JA) && !isa<VerifyJobAction>(JA)) {
4295 if (Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o))
4296 return C.addResultFile(FinalOutput->getValue(), &JA);
4297 }
4298
4299 // For /P, preprocess to file named after BaseInput.
4300 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_P)) {
4301 assert(AtTopLevel && isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA));
4302 StringRef BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
4303 StringRef NameArg;
4304 if (Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fi))
4305 NameArg = A->getValue();
4306 return C.addResultFile(
4307 MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), NameArg, BaseName, types::TY_PP_C),
4308 &JA);
4309 }
4310
4311 // Default to writing to stdout?
4312 if (AtTopLevel && !CCGenDiagnostics && isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA))
4313 return "-";
4314
4315 // Is this the assembly listing for /FA?
4316 if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm &&
4317 (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_FA) ||
4318 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa))) {
4319 // Use /Fa and the input filename to determine the asm file name.
4320 StringRef BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
4321 StringRef FaValue = C.getArgs().getLastArgValue(options::OPT__SLASH_Fa);
4322 return C.addResultFile(
4323 MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), FaValue, BaseName, JA.getType()),
4324 &JA);
4325 }
4326
4327 // Output to a temporary file?
4328 if ((!AtTopLevel && !isSaveTempsEnabled() &&
4329 !C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo)) ||
4330 CCGenDiagnostics) {
4331 StringRef Name = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
4332 std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = Name.split('.');
4333 SmallString<128> TmpName;
4334 const char *Suffix = types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode());
4335 Arg *A = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_fcrash_diagnostics_dir);
4336 if (CCGenDiagnostics && A) {
4337 SmallString<128> CrashDirectory(A->getValue());
4338 if (!getVFS().exists(CrashDirectory))
4339 llvm::sys::fs::create_directories(CrashDirectory);
4340 llvm::sys::path::append(CrashDirectory, Split.first);
4341 const char *Middle = Suffix ? "-%%%%%%." : "-%%%%%%";
4342 std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::createUniqueFile(
4343 CrashDirectory + Middle + Suffix, TmpName);
4344 if (EC) {
4345 Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
4346 return "";
4347 }
4348 } else {
4349 TmpName = GetTemporaryPath(Split.first, Suffix);
4350 }
4351 return C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpName));
4352 }
4353
4354 SmallString<128> BasePath(BaseInput);
4355 StringRef BaseName;
4356
4357 // Dsymutil actions should use the full path.
4358 if (isa<DsymutilJobAction>(JA) || isa<VerifyJobAction>(JA))
4359 BaseName = BasePath;
4360 else
4361 BaseName = llvm::sys::path::filename(BasePath);
4362
4363 // Determine what the derived output name should be.
4364 const char *NamedOutput;
4365
4366 if ((JA.getType() == types::TY_Object || JA.getType() == types::TY_LTO_BC) &&
4367 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo, options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
4368 // The /Fo or /o flag decides the object filename.
4369 StringRef Val =
4370 C.getArgs()
4371 .getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fo, options::OPT__SLASH_o)
4372 ->getValue();
4373 NamedOutput =
4374 MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), Val, BaseName, types::TY_Object);
4375 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Image &&
4376 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fe,
4377 options::OPT__SLASH_o)) {
4378 // The /Fe or /o flag names the linked file.
4379 StringRef Val =
4380 C.getArgs()
4381 .getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fe, options::OPT__SLASH_o)
4382 ->getValue();
4383 NamedOutput =
4384 MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), Val, BaseName, types::TY_Image);
4385 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Image) {
4386 if (IsCLMode()) {
4387 // clang-cl uses BaseName for the executable name.
4388 NamedOutput =
4389 MakeCLOutputFilename(C.getArgs(), "", BaseName, types::TY_Image);
4390 } else {
4391 SmallString<128> Output(getDefaultImageName());
4392 Output += OffloadingPrefix;
4393 if (MultipleArchs && !BoundArch.empty()) {
4394 Output += "-";
4395 Output.append(BoundArch);
4396 }
4397 NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Output.c_str());
4398 }
4399 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PCH && IsCLMode()) {
4400 NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(GetClPchPath(C, BaseName));
4401 } else {
4402 const char *Suffix = types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode());
4403 assert(Suffix && "All types used for output should have a suffix.");
4404
4405 std::string::size_type End = std::string::npos;
4406 if (!types::appendSuffixForType(JA.getType()))
4407 End = BaseName.rfind('.');
4408 SmallString<128> Suffixed(BaseName.substr(0, End));
4409 Suffixed += OffloadingPrefix;
4410 if (MultipleArchs && !BoundArch.empty()) {
4411 Suffixed += "-";
4412 Suffixed.append(BoundArch);
4413 }
4414 // When using both -save-temps and -emit-llvm, use a ".tmp.bc" suffix for
4415 // the unoptimized bitcode so that it does not get overwritten by the ".bc"
4416 // optimized bitcode output.
4417 if (!AtTopLevel && C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_emit_llvm) &&
4418 JA.getType() == types::TY_LLVM_BC)
4419 Suffixed += ".tmp";
4420 Suffixed += '.';
4421 Suffixed += Suffix;
4422 NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(Suffixed.c_str());
4423 }
4424
4425 // Prepend object file path if -save-temps=obj
4426 if (!AtTopLevel && isSaveTempsObj() && C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_o) &&
4427 JA.getType() != types::TY_PCH) {
4428 Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o);
4429 SmallString<128> TempPath(FinalOutput->getValue());
4430 llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(TempPath);
4431 StringRef OutputFileName = llvm::sys::path::filename(NamedOutput);
4432 llvm::sys::path::append(TempPath, OutputFileName);
4433 NamedOutput = C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TempPath.c_str());
4434 }
4435
4436 // If we're saving temps and the temp file conflicts with the input file,
4437 // then avoid overwriting input file.
4438 if (!AtTopLevel && isSaveTempsEnabled() && NamedOutput == BaseName) {
4439 bool SameFile = false;
4440 SmallString<256> Result;
4441 llvm::sys::fs::current_path(Result);
4442 llvm::sys::path::append(Result, BaseName);
4443 llvm::sys::fs::equivalent(BaseInput, Result.c_str(), SameFile);
4444 // Must share the same path to conflict.
4445 if (SameFile) {
4446 StringRef Name = llvm::sys::path::filename(BaseInput);
4447 std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = Name.split('.');
4448 std::string TmpName = GetTemporaryPath(
4449 Split.first, types::getTypeTempSuffix(JA.getType(), IsCLMode()));
4450 return C.addTempFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(TmpName));
4451 }
4452 }
4453
4454 // As an annoying special case, PCH generation doesn't strip the pathname.
4455 if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PCH && !IsCLMode()) {
4456 llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(BasePath);
4457 if (BasePath.empty())
4458 BasePath = NamedOutput;
4459 else
4460 llvm::sys::path::append(BasePath, NamedOutput);
4461 return C.addResultFile(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(BasePath.c_str()), &JA);
4462 } else {
4463 return C.addResultFile(NamedOutput, &JA);
4464 }
4465}
4466
4467std::string Driver::GetFilePath(StringRef Name, const ToolChain &TC) const {
4468 // Search for Name in a list of paths.
4469 auto SearchPaths = [&](const llvm::SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &P)
4470 -> llvm::Optional<std::string> {
4471 // Respect a limited subset of the '-Bprefix' functionality in GCC by
4472 // attempting to use this prefix when looking for file paths.
4473 for (const auto &Dir : P) {
4474 if (Dir.empty())
4475 continue;
4476 SmallString<128> P(Dir[0] == '=' ? SysRoot + Dir.substr(1) : Dir);
4477 llvm::sys::path::append(P, Name);
4478 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(P)))
4479 return P.str().str();
4480 }
4481 return None;
4482 };
4483
4484 if (auto P = SearchPaths(PrefixDirs))
4485 return *P;
4486
4487 SmallString<128> R(ResourceDir);
4488 llvm::sys::path::append(R, Name);
4489 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(R)))
4490 return R.str();
4491
4492 SmallString<128> P(TC.getCompilerRTPath());
4493 llvm::sys::path::append(P, Name);
4494 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(P)))
4495 return P.str();
4496
4497 SmallString<128> D(Dir);
4498 llvm::sys::path::append(D, "..", Name);
4499 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(Twine(D)))
4500 return D.str();
4501
4502 if (auto P = SearchPaths(TC.getLibraryPaths()))
4503 return *P;
4504
4505 if (auto P = SearchPaths(TC.getFilePaths()))
4506 return *P;
4507
4508 return Name;
4509}
4510
4511void Driver::generatePrefixedToolNames(
4512 StringRef Tool, const ToolChain &TC,
4513 SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Names) const {
4514 // FIXME: Needs a better variable than TargetTriple
4515 Names.emplace_back((TargetTriple + "-" + Tool).str());
4516 Names.emplace_back(Tool);
4517
4518 // Allow the discovery of tools prefixed with LLVM's default target triple.
4519 std::string DefaultTargetTriple = llvm::sys::getDefaultTargetTriple();
4520 if (DefaultTargetTriple != TargetTriple)
4521 Names.emplace_back((DefaultTargetTriple + "-" + Tool).str());
4522}
4523
4524static bool ScanDirForExecutable(SmallString<128> &Dir,
4525 ArrayRef<std::string> Names) {
4526 for (const auto &Name : Names) {
4527 llvm::sys::path::append(Dir, Name);
4528 if (llvm::sys::fs::can_execute(Twine(Dir)))
4529 return true;
4530 llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(Dir);
4531 }
4532 return false;
4533}
4534
4535std::string Driver::GetProgramPath(StringRef Name, const ToolChain &TC) const {
4536 SmallVector<std::string, 2> TargetSpecificExecutables;
4537 generatePrefixedToolNames(Name, TC, TargetSpecificExecutables);
4538
4539 // Respect a limited subset of the '-Bprefix' functionality in GCC by
4540 // attempting to use this prefix when looking for program paths.
4541 for (const auto &PrefixDir : PrefixDirs) {
4542 if (llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(PrefixDir)) {
4543 SmallString<128> P(PrefixDir);
4544 if (ScanDirForExecutable(P, TargetSpecificExecutables))
4545 return P.str();
4546 } else {
4547 SmallString<128> P((PrefixDir + Name).str());
4548 if (llvm::sys::fs::can_execute(Twine(P)))
4549 return P.str();
4550 }
4551 }
4552
4553 const ToolChain::path_list &List = TC.getProgramPaths();
4554 for (const auto &Path : List) {
4555 SmallString<128> P(Path);
4556 if (ScanDirForExecutable(P, TargetSpecificExecutables))
4557 return P.str();
4558 }
4559
4560 // If all else failed, search the path.
4561 for (const auto &TargetSpecificExecutable : TargetSpecificExecutables)
4562 if (llvm::ErrorOr<std::string> P =
4563 llvm::sys::findProgramByName(TargetSpecificExecutable))
4564 return *P;
4565
4566 return Name;
4567}

4569std::string Driver::GetTemporaryPath(StringRef Prefix, StringRef Suffix) const {
4570 SmallString<128> Path;
4571 std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::createTemporaryFile(Prefix, Suffix, Path);
4572 if (EC) {
4573 Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
4574 return "";
4575 }
4576
4577 return Path.str();
4578}

4580std::string Driver::GetTemporaryDirectory(StringRef Prefix) const {
4581 SmallString<128> Path;
4582 std::error_code EC = llvm::sys::fs::createUniqueDirectory(Prefix, Path);
4583 if (EC) {
4584 Diag(clang::diag::err_unable_to_make_temp) << EC.message();
4585 return "";
4586 }
4587
4588 return Path.str();

4590
4591std::string Driver::GetClPchPath(Compilation &C, StringRef BaseName) const {
4592 SmallString<128> Output;
4593 if (Arg *FpArg = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Fp)) {
4594 // FIXME: If anybody needs it, implement this obscure rule:
4595 // "If you specify a directory without a file name, the default file name
4596 // is VCx0.pch., where x is the major version of Visual C++ in use."
4597 Output = FpArg->getValue();
4598
4599 // "If you do not specify an extension as part of the path name, an
4600 // extension of .pch is assumed. "
4601 if (!llvm::sys::path::has_extension(Output))
4602 Output += ".pch";
4603 } else {
4604 if (Arg *YcArg = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc))
4605 Output = YcArg->getValue();
4606 if (Output.empty())
4607 Output = BaseName;
4608 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Output, ".pch");
4609 }
4610 return Output.str();
4611}
4612
4613const ToolChain &Driver::getToolChain(const ArgList &Args,
4614 const llvm::Triple &Target) const {
4615
4616 auto &TC = ToolChains[Target.str()];
4617 if (!TC) {
4618 switch (Target.getOS()) {
4619 case llvm::Triple::Haiku:
4620 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Haiku>(*this, Target, Args);
4621 break;
4622 case llvm::Triple::Ananas:
4623 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Ananas>(*this, Target, Args);
4624 break;
4625 case llvm::Triple::CloudABI:
4626 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::CloudABI>(*this, Target, Args);
4627 break;
4628 case llvm::Triple::Darwin:
4629 case llvm::Triple::MacOSX:
4630 case llvm::Triple::IOS:
4631 case llvm::Triple::TvOS:
4632 case llvm::Triple::WatchOS:
4633 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::DarwinClang>(*this, Target, Args);
4634 break;
4635 case llvm::Triple::DragonFly:
4636 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::DragonFly>(*this, Target, Args);
4637 break;
4638 case llvm::Triple::OpenBSD:
4639 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::OpenBSD>(*this, Target, Args);
4640 break;
4641 case llvm::Triple::NetBSD:
4642 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::NetBSD>(*this, Target, Args);
4643 break;
4644 case llvm::Triple::FreeBSD:
4645 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::FreeBSD>(*this, Target, Args);
4646 break;
4647 case llvm::Triple::Minix:
4648 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Minix>(*this, Target, Args);
4649 break;
4650 case llvm::Triple::Linux:
4651 case llvm::Triple::ELFIAMCU:
4652 if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::hexagon)
4653 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::HexagonToolChain>(*this, Target,
4654 Args);
4655 else if ((Target.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::MipsTechnologies) &&
4656 !Target.hasEnvironment())
4657 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MipsLLVMToolChain>(*this, Target,
4658 Args);
4659 else if (Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::ppc ||
4660 Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::ppc64 ||
4661 Target.getArch() == llvm::Triple::ppc64le)
4662 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::PPCLinuxToolChain>(*this, Target,
4663 Args);
4664 else
4665 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Linux>(*this, Target, Args);
4666 break;
4667 case llvm::Triple::NaCl:
4668 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::NaClToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4669 break;
4670 case llvm::Triple::Fuchsia:
4671 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Fuchsia>(*this, Target, Args);
4672 break;
4673 case llvm::Triple::Solaris:
4674 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Solaris>(*this, Target, Args);
4675 break;
4676 case llvm::Triple::AMDHSA:
4677 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::AMDGPUToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4678 break;
4679 case llvm::Triple::Win32:
4680 switch (Target.getEnvironment()) {
4681 default:
4682 if (Target.isOSBinFormatELF())
4683 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_ELF>(*this, Target, Args);
4684 else if (Target.isOSBinFormatMachO())
4685 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MachO>(*this, Target, Args);
4686 else
4687 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_GCC>(*this, Target, Args);
4688 break;
4689 case llvm::Triple::GNU:
4690 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MinGW>(*this, Target, Args);
4691 break;
4692 case llvm::Triple::Itanium:
4693 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::CrossWindowsToolChain>(*this, Target,
4694 Args);
4695 break;
4696 case llvm::Triple::MSVC:
4697 case llvm::Triple::UnknownEnvironment:
4698 if (Args.getLastArgValue(options::OPT_fuse_ld_EQ)
4699 .startswith_lower("bfd"))
4700 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::CrossWindowsToolChain>(
4701 *this, Target, Args);
4702 else
4703 TC =
4704 llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MSVCToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4705 break;
4706 }
4707 break;
4708 case llvm::Triple::PS4:
4709 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::PS4CPU>(*this, Target, Args);
4710 break;
4711 case llvm::Triple::Contiki:
4712 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Contiki>(*this, Target, Args);
4713 break;
4714 case llvm::Triple::Hurd:
4715 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Hurd>(*this, Target, Args);
4716 break;
4717 case llvm::Triple::RTEMS:
4718 if (Target.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::Myriad)
4719 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MyriadToolChain>(*this, Target,
4720 Args);
4721 else
4722 // FIXME: This will probably break the x86 rtems build but should work for MIPS/CHERI
4723 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::RTEMS>(*this, Target, Args);
4724 break;
4725 default:
4726 // Of these targets, Hexagon is the only one that might have
4727 // an OS of Linux, in which case it got handled above already.
4728 switch (Target.getArch()) {
4729 case llvm::Triple::tce:
4730 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::TCEToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4731 break;
4732 case llvm::Triple::tcele:
4733 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::TCELEToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4734 break;
4735 case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
4736 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::HexagonToolChain>(*this, Target,
4737 Args);
4738 break;
4739 case llvm::Triple::lanai:
4740 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::LanaiToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4741 break;
4742 case llvm::Triple::xcore:
4743 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::XCoreToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4744 break;
4745 case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
4746 case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
4747 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::WebAssembly>(*this, Target, Args);
4748 break;
4749 case llvm::Triple::avr:
4750 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::AVRToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4751 break;
4752 case llvm::Triple::msp430:
4753 TC =
4754 llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MSP430ToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4755 break;
4756 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
4757 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
4758 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::RISCVToolChain>(*this, Target, Args);
4759 break;
4760 default:
4761 if (Target.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::Myriad)
4762 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MyriadToolChain>(*this, Target,
4763 Args);
4764 else if (toolchains::BareMetal::handlesTarget(Target))
4765 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::BareMetal>(*this, Target, Args);
4766 else if (Target.isOSBinFormatELF())
4767 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_ELF>(*this, Target, Args);
4768 else if (Target.isOSBinFormatMachO())
4769 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::MachO>(*this, Target, Args);
4770 else
4771 TC = llvm::make_unique<toolchains::Generic_GCC>(*this, Target, Args);
4772 }
4773 }
4774 }
4775
4776 // Intentionally omitted from the switch above: llvm::Triple::CUDA. CUDA
4777 // compiles always need two toolchains, the CUDA toolchain and the host
4778 // toolchain. So the only valid way to create a CUDA toolchain is via
4779 // CreateOffloadingDeviceToolChains.
4780
4781 return *TC;
4782}
4783
4784bool Driver::ShouldUseClangCompiler(const JobAction &JA) const {
4785 // Say "no" if there is not exactly one input of a type clang understands.
4786 if (JA.size() != 1 ||
4787 !types::isAcceptedByClang((*JA.input_begin())->getType()))
4788 return false;
4789
4790 // And say "no" if this is not a kind of action clang understands.
4791 if (!isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA) && !isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA) &&
4792 !isa<CompileJobAction>(JA) && !isa<BackendJobAction>(JA))
4793 return false;
4794
4795 return true;
4796}

4798/// GetReleaseVersion - Parse (([0-9]+)(.([0-9]+)(.([0-9]+)?))?)? and return the
4799/// grouped values as integers. Numbers which are not provided are set to 0.
4800///
4801/// \return True if the entire string was parsed (9.2), or all groups were
4802/// parsed (10.3.5extrastuff).
4803bool Driver::GetReleaseVersion(StringRef Str, unsigned &Major, unsigned &Minor,
4804 unsigned &Micro, bool &HadExtra) {
4805 HadExtra = false;
4806
4807 Major = Minor = Micro = 0;
4808 if (Str.empty())
4809 return false;
4810
4811 if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Major))
4812 return false;
4813 if (Str.empty())
4814 return true;
4815 if (Str[0] != '.')
4816 return false;
4817
4818 Str = Str.drop_front(1);
4819
4820 if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Minor))
4821 return false;
4822 if (Str.empty())
4823 return true;
4824 if (Str[0] != '.')
4825 return false;
4826 Str = Str.drop_front(1);
4827
4828 if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Micro))
4829 return false;
4830 if (!Str.empty())
4831 HadExtra = true;
4832 return true;
4833}
4834
4835/// Parse digits from a string \p Str and fulfill \p Digits with
4836/// the parsed numbers. This method assumes that the max number of
4837/// digits to look for is equal to Digits.size().
4838///
4839/// \return True if the entire string was parsed and there are
4840/// no extra characters remaining at the end.
4841bool Driver::GetReleaseVersion(StringRef Str,
4842 MutableArrayRef<unsigned> Digits) {
4843 if (Str.empty())
4844 return false;
4845
4846 unsigned CurDigit = 0;
4847 while (CurDigit < Digits.size()) {
4848 unsigned Digit;
4849 if (Str.consumeInteger(10, Digit))
4850 return false;
4851 Digits[CurDigit] = Digit;
4852 if (Str.empty())
4853 return true;
4854 if (Str[0] != '.')
4855 return false;
4856 Str = Str.drop_front(1);
4857 CurDigit++;
4858 }
4859
4860 // More digits than requested, bail out...
4861 return false;
4862}

4864std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>
4865Driver::getIncludeExcludeOptionFlagMasks(bool IsClCompatMode) const {
4866 unsigned IncludedFlagsBitmask = 0;
4867 unsigned ExcludedFlagsBitmask = options::NoDriverOption;
4868
4869 if (IsClCompatMode) {
4870 // Include CL and Core options.
4871 IncludedFlagsBitmask |= options::CLOption;
4872 IncludedFlagsBitmask |= options::CoreOption;
4873 } else {
4874 ExcludedFlagsBitmask |= options::CLOption;
4875 }
4876
4877 return std::make_pair(IncludedFlagsBitmask, ExcludedFlagsBitmask);
4878}
